animal.description:
Zeus

1 and a 1/2 yrs old 

German Shepherd Mix

Zeus has a great temperament, is dog friendly, and loves people. He is neutered and UTD on all vaccines. 

Foster or adopter needed! Transport date to be determined.

We are posting this dog because its in need of rescue! We are looking for a foster or foster-to-adopt (a pre approved adopter who intends to adopt the dog). animal.description:
Meet Bryce! This handsome boy is 4 years old and weighs 52lbs. He is just as sweet as can be!

He loves to be with people and has done well with the dogs hes met! He has not been tested with cats.

He has occasional accidents in his kennel but he is in a boarding situation and with a good routine he will get it in no time!

He does well in a kennel but really wants to be out with people and soak up all the loves!

He pulls a little bit on a leash but takes correction well.

He would love a home with previous Bully breed experience to continue his training and help him be the best boy he can be! He leaves Houston on 2/6 and arrives on the transport truck on 2/8!

Please fill out an application to be considered.

With any additional questions please email tiffany@threelittlepittiesrescue.org for more information on making Bryce part of your family!

animal.description:
Rogue was found roaming with 2 other huskies, who we belive are his siblings. The finder brought them home and has done an incredible job of taking care of them and training them! We believe them to be between 1-2 years of age. 

Rogue: is most likely the oldest and hes the leader of their little gang! He loves affection and isnt scared to paw at you when he isnt done being loved on. Gets very attached and wants to please! 
 

Here is some information their foster has shared about him and his siblings: 


All dogs seem to have grown up together but are not bonded and can be adopted separately. They did better than I thought they would do getting baths as long as you go slow and talk to them! They did so great at the dog park. They are learning different ways to play (when they play together they are boys but my brothers female dog Lucy doesnt play rough) Did not seem to know basic commands but have been working on sit and off (jumping). They are required and successfully sit for 15-30 seconds (depending on my mood) before their food is placed in front of them for breakfast and dinner. Not food aggressive at all! As a matter of fact each dog will stop eating to show you attention if you ask them for it. I was able to put my hand in the bowl while they are each eating without fear. Individually each dog met my cats but completely supervised and controlled. Together they seem to want to play with my 10 year old cat and its just too much causing him to run and them to give chase. I have separate inside time between my cats and the dogs. We are doing much better about accidents in the home. The first week they had 4 plus accidents a day. Now have only had 2 accidents in the past 3 weeks. They (Rogue and Sammy) when left alone and bored they chew on whatever is lying around, definitely need a job to do or lots of fun toys or Kong's! Thankfully they do not constantly bark and dont bark at absolutely everything (park on other side of chain link fence where kids and other dogs walk) but are always alert. They love fetch and we are working on the returning part in the game of fetch.

Rogue would love to be part of any family and being a husky would like a family that is active or has a back yard for him to play in.

He is up to date on vaccines according to his age, has received proper deworming, and comes with additional dewormer. He is microchipped, neutered, comes with 6 months of preventatives, one month free trial of pet insurance, all of our animals receive a health certificate (this states a licensed veterinary saw the pet and deemed it healthy for travel, it is not a promise of perfect health.) Our transports are USDA certified and tfransport is included in adoption fee!

He is currently being fostered in Houston, Tx but will be traveling to the PNW 2/6/21.

Please inquire by submitting an application to mariah@threelittlepittiesrescue.org

Application link: https://petstablished.com/adoption_form/26842/generic

animal.description:
Meet Folgers! 

Folgers is currently 8 weeks old and is ready to travel to the PNW on 12/06 and arrive on 12/08. He is an American Staffordshire Terrier mix and his momma is gorgeous! Folgers is estimated to weigh about 55 pounds when full grown. Him and his brother(now adopted) love to eat, sleep, play & repeat! We would love for Folgers to grow up in a home with other pup siblings so he can socialize as he grows! Since he is a pitty, we will mostly be looking at owned homes for this little guy! 

 

He is up to date on vaccines according to age, has received proper deworming, and comes with additional dewormer if needed. This pet is microchipped, spayed/neutered, comes with 2-6 months of Heartworm preventative, and one month free trial of pet insurance if registered by adopter with insurance company. All animals receive a health certificate (stating that a licensed veterinarian saw the pet and deemed it healthy for travel, but is not a promise of perfect health.) Our transports are USDA certified and the cost of transport is included in adoption fee!

He is currently being fostered in Houston, TX but will be traveling to the PNW once adopted

Due to the Covid-19 crisis we are experiencing a dramatic influx in inquiries and adoption applications. If you have questions regarding a pup you are interested in please fill out an adoption application. Once received it can take up to a week to complete our review. animal.description:
Meet Bear Jugs!

Bear is a sweet big fur baby! He is a Shepherd mix about 1-2 years old and 50 lbs. He is very friendly and loves other dogs. He is in foster care with a 7 lb Shih-Tzu and does well with little dogs as well. He's been around teenage teenagers and does well with them! He would be best suited with older children. He comes when called. He can sit, shake, lay on command. He's potty trained and he's familar with the crate and he goes into the crate when asked.He'll need somone to continue with his crate training. He loves to exercise and needs daily exercise. He will do amazing in an active household who love to hike, run, jog, and camping. He is an intelligent dog and eager to please. He also thinks he's a lap dog, but he may be too big for that. He loves to be by his person and loves to be involved with his family. He loves to play fetch and loves chew toys. He is an amazing dog and he'd be a great companion for someone! 

He is currently being fostered in Houston,TX and is eligible to travel 2/06 once he finds the perfect home!

For any inquires or questions please contact violet@threelittlepittiesrescue.org

To apply for this gentle sweetheart please fill out an application in order to be considered: https://petstablished.com/adoption_form/30285/generic

animal.description:
Meet Onyx Nicole!

Onyx is a sweetheart that will fill your heart with joy! We think she is a Shepherd/Collie mix and about 4 months old and 24 lbs. She is a show stopper, friendly, active, and a lovable little one. She is full of playfulness and puppy energy! She is curious and a natural leader. She doesn't mind bubble baths and she wouldn't mind another brother or sister to play with. She enjoys other dogs big and small, she is very intelligent. She needs mental stimulation and daily exercise to keep this girl happy. She loves to play and she would fit in with an active household. She loves kids and she would be an amazing family pet. She would love to be with a family that enjoys hiking,running, or jogging. Puppies require a lot of patience and a lot of time to work with. She needs someone that is patient and kind. She is not completely potty trained since she is a baby still. She will need basic obedience and socialization right from the start. Puppies are a long-term commitment and we need to find families who are commited to training her. She is excited to meet her family in the PNW!

She is up to date on vaccines according to her age, she has received proper deworming, and comes with additional dewormer. She is microchipped, spayed, comes with 2-6 months of preventatives, one month free trial of pet insurance, all of our animals receive a health certificate (this states a licensed veterinary saw the pet and deemed it healthy for travel, it is not a promise of perfect health.) Our transports are USDA certified and tfransport is included in adoption fee!

She is currently being fostered in Houston, Tx but will be traveling to the PNW as soon as she finds her perfect home!

email violet@threelittlepittiesrescue.org for inquires and questions

animal.description: This adorable Shar Pei is Chloe and she is super sweet. Chloe was a little nervous when she first arrived, so it took a moment to win her over; it's possible that she may be the same way with other new people. Miss Chloe loves to shower you with affection. She gets the zoomies, jumps up an down (you may end up with some scratches on your arms, because she's just so excited to be with you), and loves life. Chloe likes toys, but it depends on the toy. She LOVES squeaky plush toys; the zoomies really come out then. Shar Pei's are an interesting breed, so make sure you do your homework. We think it would be best if she went to a home with older kids, 12 and older; other dogs are a possibility, we can have a meet and greet to see how they get along. Cats are also a possibility; Chloe didn't show much interest when we cat tested her, but we can always test her again if needed.

animal.description:
Meet this loveable pal, Buddy. Buddy is a 14yr old, 71 lb Blue Nose American Staffordshire Terrier who his foster momma calls a lump of love. He is a sweet, gentle, and laid back guy who is happy to Netflix and chill. He does well with other calm dogs, but would do best without cats. Buddy is blind, so he must go to a home with no stairs and no pool, no exceptions. Otherwise this handsome guy has no medical issues and is looking for a home he can call his for the rest of his days. Once he learns his home he can navigate around very well. Buddy is house trained when kept on a schedule, and he enjoys sleeping peacefully through the night in his orthopedic dog bed. Buddy is currently being fostered in Sumter County.

If you think youre the best friend to take care of Buddy, fill out the adoption application at www.PoodleandPoochRescue.org and well see if its a match. Buddy is up to date on vaccines, neutered, heart worm negative, microchipped, and ready for his forever home. His adoption fee has been sponsored.

animal.description:
Ollie is an incredibly sweet and calm boy. He loves all humans, big and small, along with every pet we have encountered so far. Ollie loves a good game of tug-a-war with his rope followed by some relaxing and napping. If you're looking for a gentle, affectionate, little guy - Ollie is your guy!

Ollie's foster home includes three children and prior to that he was in a home with a cat. He is house broken and crate trained, and he understands basic commands such as "stay", "off", and "come." Ollie is a hugger and will great you by going up on his hind legs and embracing you with his front paws while showing you all of his teeth and giving you the biggest doggy smile we have ever seen! 

Behavioral issues include begging for human food and sneaking into trash when accessible. Ollie is also very sensitive about his front paws being touched but has never shown aggression in trying to avoid it (note: he gets his paws wiped before entering the house regularly so he is getting used to them being touched). He needs to lose a little weight but he's working on that now!

Our Adoption Process:


	Meet the Adoption Criteria. Before you do anything else, make sure you meet our adoption criteria. You must be at least 21 years old. You must live within a 60-mile radius of Richardson, Texas. You must share veterinary records for all pets currently in your home and all pets owned in the last five years. All pets in the home must be spayed or neutered. If you rent your home, you must provide verification that pets are allowed on the property. You must be willing to be interviewed by an adoption counselor and you must undergo an in person or virtual home visit from an RHS representative.
	Complete Application. https://www.petstablished.com/adoption_form/14314/generic
	Phone Interview. Compatible applicants will be forwarded to a counselor who will contact the applicant for a phone interview.
	Home Visit. If all the steps above are completed satisfactorily, we will set up a visit where you can meet the pet you are interested in. We will try to include the foster parent so you can learn more about how the pet is in a home environment.
	Complete Adoption. If all feel it is a good match, we will schedule the adoption at your home or an off-site location. The applicant will need to complete the adoption contract and pay the adoption fee. Our adoption fee is $250 for adult dogs, $300 for puppies (under 1 year) and $125 for cats. Discounts are available for senior-aged pets.

animal.description:
Sam
Male
Age: 4 years old
Weight: 95 lbs
Breed: German Shepherd mix

Hey there! Sam is the name, stuffed toys and stinky farts are my game! I'm the sweetest boy who loves to give all the kisses! I love going on adventures that involve a car followed by lots of walks! I just love being wherever my human is! That includes being your sous chef in the kitchen or even lounging and watching my favorite movie, Shrek!

I have shown to have some anxiety and constantly need to be reassured by my human that everything is OK; so a calm home would be ideal for me! I would prefer to be the only fur child in my forever home and children 10 years or older would be perfect! I am house trained and crate trained with the help of a frozen peanut butter Kong; I love peanut butter!! I would much rather not go into a crate because I'm such a good boy and just lay around until my foster mom comes home to play. I know sit, paw/shake, down and no. I'm working on stay, come, and inside voice. I also walk very well on a leash so long as another pesky critter isnt nearby; those squirrels are so squirrely!

I am quite the perfect package and know Ill make the perfect addition to the prefect family!

If you are interested in meeting sweet Sam, apply to adopt at www.causeforcanines.org Adoption fee $250
Children must be 10 years old or older
Must be an Ohio Resident at least 25 years old or older.

animal.description: Cupid has had a hard time in his short 5 years of life. However, he still lives up to his name and is a big lover! Cupid may have escaped a backyard breeding situation when he was found wondering around Raleigh. After going through professional training, he was adopted out to a wonderful man who owned a boat. Him and his owner became inseparable and Cupid became a boat dog. Recently, his owner passed away very unexpectedly and Cupid has returned to his former fosters. He is crate trained like a champ, is house trained, and knows commands such as sit, down, stay and crate. Cupid loves to play, and to play hard! He will need a fenced yard in his forever home. He has the energy that could keep up with a marathon runner but will snuggle up any chance he can get. Cupid just loves to be with his person and is extremely loyal. He gets along with his two foster doggy sisters and has been a huge hit when being out on the town. If you're looking for a big-headed, goofy, energetic lover-- look no further! Cupid is your man! If you are interested in this animal please start by filling out an adoption application at CFP-NC.org/adopt and we will get in touch with you.

animal.description:
Jackson is estimated to be around a year old and is a pitbull/Great Dane mix. He is a little over 50lbs and is neutered and up to date on vaccines. He is very energetic and dog friendly but can play a little rough. Jackson is kid friendly. Hes been around a four year old and did good with him. He likes to chase cats, he hasnt hurt them but does chase them. He is house trained but will have an accident here and there if he isn't taken out often enough but with a structured schedule this shouldn't be an issue. 

Once Jackson has all of his energy burnt out he is such a cuddle bug. He would love nothing more than to find a home where he can snuggle with his human. 

Please apply at crossyourpaws.com if you are interested in giving him a forever home.

If you have an application on file- please message us on Facebook -do not email! 

We are a 100% volunteer 501c3 and rely solely on donations of our supporters and volunteers.

RCHS does not conduct DNA tests on dogs who enter our facility therefore we are unable to guarantee breed or breed mix. Information provided by shelter staff, volunteers, and veterinarians is used to give a best estimate as to a dog's breed make up. We do our best to inform adopters about the potential breeds for each dog.

We are a dog only facility so we do not know how most of our dogs will be with cats. Even if a dog is surrendered to us and said to be good with cats there is no way to be sure the dog will be good with your cats. We do have a 7 day foster-to-adopt program so that you can see how the dog interacts with your cats before adoption.

animal.description: 0121025 - My name is Legend. Im a very sweet, happy and goofy big boy. Thankfully I was saved from the euthanasia list in New Mexico. Im a 10 month old Border Collie mix and weigh about 65lbs. I have puppy energy at times and other times Im mellow and enjoy gnawing on a bone or being cuddled. Ive only been in Colorado a short bit but Im already learning the ropes. It wont take me long to get accustomed to my forever home. Im potty trained, crate trained and sleep all night. I need a bit more work on leash walking but Im doing well so far. I enjoy playing with the dogs in my foster home but kitties are fluffy toys to me so a home without cats is needed. As Im a big, strong guy a home with older kids 12+ is required as is a yard. I love being outdoors and would probably be a great outdoorsy dog for hiking etc. Please fill out an application to adopt me at www.sloppykisses.org/adoptions!

animal.description:
Shadow is a shy guy. He was raised as a homebody and is not well-traveled. His first trip off of his property has been to the shelter and he isn't very impressed with his new surroundings. He's a sweet boy who is just so unsure of what to do now. He seems to be good with other dogs and we think with a little help from a patient person or family he would become quite the loving pup we believe he can be. His owner had to move to assisted living and unable to take him with him. He was loved very much by his owner, he lived in a home, and is house trained. Since his owner was older he is not well versed in walking on a leash, but he's learning. Shadow, lovingly nicknamed Eeyore by the staff, is a short & stocky guy, weighing in at 52 lbs at just under knee high. He has a body built like a Bassett hound including the knobby knees. He's a beautiful black brindle color. We were told he is 2 years old and has been made current on vaccines. Please consider adding this sweet, unique boy to your family. 

We offer a 7 day foster-to-adopt program so you can see if Shadow fits into your family before committing to adoption. 

We have no way to test for cat or other small animal compatibility. However, we do offer a 7 day foster-to-adopt program to those who live within an hour of Chillicothe, OH. This will allow you time to figure out if this dog is compatible for you. If not, simply bring the dog back and if it's a great fit you just come back and adopt. 

If you are interested in one of our dogs please go to rosscountyhumanesociety.org and fill out the online application. Once approved we will contact you to schedule an appointment to meet the dog.RCHS does not conduct DNA tests on dogs who enter our facility therefore we are unable to guarantee breed or breed mix. Information provided by shelter staff, volunteers, and veterinarians is used to give a best estimate as to a dog's breed make up. We do our best to inform adopters about the potential breeds for each dog.

We are a dog only facility so we do not know how most of our dogs will be with cats. We do have a 7 day foster-to-adopt program so that you can see how the dog interacts with your cats before adoption.

animal.description:
Meet Maisy! This loveable pup was surrendered to DCHS due to unfortunate 
circumstances but at no fault of her own. At about 2 years old and 15 pounds she is a great little lady who loves just about everyone once given some time to warm up. Once she's comfortable with her surroundings Maisy would love to be a lap dog. She also enjoys long walks (sits well to put on her harness and sweater), soft squeaky toys, treats, and sharing a bed with her humans. She aspires to be a great watch dog as she likes to warn you anytime someone/something is near! She is however very food motivated so redirection when necessary should be fairly easy. 

Placement Recommendations:
Owner Experience Level: Some Experience
Cats: Yes
Dogs: Yes
Kids: Middle School +Want to know more? Please call us! We've found that back and forth via email regarding a specific animal is not always effective and quick because our email is not monitored on a regular basis. So, for specific information regarding this wonderful pet, please contact one of our adoption counselors at (715) 232-9790. They are available between the hours of 8 am and 7 pm (7 days a week, excluding holidays). Thanks for your interest!

animal.description:
Hi there, my name is Leo and I'm a VERY big boy, but I am a huge softie. I came to Stray Haven as part of a transport from a high kill shelter in North Carolina, but it just so happens a manager at the shelter was friends with my former owner. They learned that the dog I lived with didn't like me at all and would bully me constantly. It got so bad that my family felt I needed to be re-homed and my mom really wanted me to come to Stray Haven because she felt I'd find a great home here. I am pretty much perfect. I have lived with kids, other dogs (there was a chihuahua and a Rottweiler mix in the home I got along great with), cats, chickens, rabbits, livestock. My family had 100 acres so we often got to run and play and frolic. I also learned that trampolines are so much fun, especially when kids are playing with me. I don't really like baths or to be sprayed with water but I do like to dip my feet into a good pond or creek to explore the shores. I am super duper housetrained and my mom said I am crate trained as well. Although I wasn't left alone often, I am a great boy in my crate. I am very food motivated and get so excited about food, so I'm easy to train and already know ""sit,"" ""down,"" and ""stay"" but may also need some brush ups when I get to my new home. I love that there's a big yard for me to play and romp and have fun. And although I'm ok on leash, I didn't do a lot of that in my previous home, so I'll need some work in this area. The staff says I will easily find a home, and I hope that's true. I'm enjoying my time at Stray Haven but I'd sure love to find a home and truly get to experience all this new stuff to me called snow. It seems like so much fun! And I just have so much love to give, I hope I find a home soon. Ask about me today!
Stray Haven Humane Society & SPCA
194 Shepard Rd., Waverly, NY 14892
(607) 565-2859, www.strayhavenspca.org 
Open hours (winter): Tues, Wed & Thurs Noon - 6pm; Sat 10am-4pm

animal.description:
Hi there! My name is Lexi and I'm a 7 month old Great Dane mix. I came all the way up here from North Carolina. I am a bit on the shy side but once I warm up I'm the goofiest girl you'll ever meet! I am such a loving girl. I love pets and attention. I could sit at your feet all day if you'd let me. I follow the caretakers around here and I'm obsessed with them. They gave me a big yard to run around in! I'm not quite sure how I feel about the snow yet but I'm getting used to it. I'm kinda lazy. I spend most of my day napping with short bursts of energy when I'm outside!. I did live with other dogs and my former owner said I could jump 5 foot fences. Just something to know if you're considering me. Of course with lots of walks and exercise, I'd have no need to leave. Since I'm just a pup and quite tall, make sure you're ready for all the action I'll bring to your life. I bring new meaning to the term ""puppy proofing."" :)

If you wanna come meet my sweet face, come on down to Stray Haven!

animal.description:
Well, hey there! They call me Dan, Handsome Dan. I'm a 3 year old Hound mix and I came from a shelter in North Carolina. I was found as a stray so there isn't much anyone knows about my history. I'm looking for my second chance here! I'm ready for my fur-ever family! I have A LOT of energy. I zoom every time I get to free run in the big yard out there! I am obsessed with the snow! I love to bury my face in it and get crazy zoomies. I don't like to sit still. I like to be busy and do something! Don't worry, I do have my down time and get some naps in but I would rather be on the move, exploring the day. I seem to get along with female dogs instead of males. I am very stand offish when it comes to male dogs. I have just been neutered so maybe my stance has changed but the staff hasn't gotten a chance to introduce me yet. If you're active and looking for a cool pal to go on an adventure, I'm your guy! Stop down to Stray Haven to say hi! I'll be waiting for you.

Adoption fee of $75.00 for kittens (6 months and under) and $60.00 for adult cats. 
Dogs are $100 and $125 for puppies (6 months and under) plus sales tax and includes:
- spay/neuter surgery
- rabies
- voucher for rabies vaccine (if too young)
- first distemper-parvo and bordetella vaccinations (dogs)
- vaccinations and feline leukemia test (cats)
- de-worming 
-microchipping (dogs)

Dog adopters are also invited to our free obedience class. Animals as young as eight weeks of age may be spayed/neutered, and the surgery is done before the pet goes to its new home. Local veterinarians work with the DBCHS to make the surgery affordable so we can keep our adoption fees low. For more information about adoption, call (859) 238-1117 or email us at dbchs@bellsouth.net

animal.description:
In a world of energetic Aussies, Elsa is laidback Aussie doodle who loves to be cuddled by her person. Calm and quiet, Elsa is about 3 years old and 35 pounds. She likes to be curled up on her bed near her humans, but will jump in and join a game of chase with her canine friends if the opportunity arises.

Elsa is hearing and vision impaired so she is working on touch commands. She is very smart and is already house trained and crate trained. She loves going on walks and is spectacular on a leash. She would do well in a home that is relatively quiet and she needs a fenced-in yard for safe adventures. If you have snuggles and love for Elsa, please reach out.

Elsa is up to date on vaccinations, spayed, microchipped, and current on heartworm/flea and tick prevention. Also included in her adoption is a Fi GPS collar and one year of GPS service subscription. animal.description: This sweet, silly boy is Squiggles! His interests include cuddles, naps, long walks, sniffing around, car rides, earning treats, and licking faces. He loves all people and is happiest in a home full of humans. Squiggles can be slower to warm up to men he doesn't know, but he warms up quickly, and before long, he will roll on his back and ask for a belly rub. Squiggles is a long and lean pup still developing coordination, but he is learning to walk very well on a harness and enjoys all the people who stop and tell him how handsome he is. He's also a smart pup who will do anything for his favorite meatball treats and already knows some basic commands like sit and down. He truly lives to make his humans happy, and for such a young dog, he listens very well. Born to be a loyal companion, he does very well when with his humans. He has little interest in running around the yard alone, instead preferring to lay quietly by his human's side until they need him. When he needs to go potty, he heads straight to the door and politely waits to be let out. Squiggles hasn't had any accidents so far! He also loves his chew toys and knows to leave household items alone, unless they smell like food! Squiggles is a pro at crate training but has also done well left to roam the bedroom. He may whine for a few minutes when people go, though he is fast to fall asleep when waiting for his humans to return. While he is also quick to investigate strange noises, he saves his powerful bark for when he really has something to say. He can be fairly submissive around other dogs and cats in the home, but any squirrels in the yard better watch out! This young pup still has lots to learn but is sweet and eager to please! Are you ready to teach him to be the best boy!

animal.description: If you would like to have a fan who loves watching you and wants your autograph, come meet Spudz. This very sweet boy loves sitting by you, and will gaze at you with love. He'll also hope for your petting! He's also always happy to meet new people, just wanting their pets, too. This very smart boy gets up in the morning with a burst of energy, wanting to go outside for playtime and short walks. He walks calmly on his leash, not reacting to other dogs he sees. At home, he likes playing with his doggie housemate and the teenager he lives with. He's also living nicely with a cat, although they stay in separate rooms. He has recovered from parvo and is beginning to learn basic commands, now understanding 'sit.' And he is also house-trained. Spudz has some separation anxiety that makes him always want to be with his humans. He would do well in a home with patient, loving people who are home a lot and can help him feel confident and secure when they are out. He'd also love a calm canine companion. Come meet this adorable boy!

Meet Viking!  He's a handsome young male mix, ready for fun and adventure!  He's very ball motivated and fetch seems to be his favorite activity - even more than treats!  Viking is friendly with humans, but has been reactive to some of our other male dogs.  He's medium/large with a beautiful brindle coat.  Viking is only about a year old, a high energy guy looking for an active household!  If you love to throw a ball, Viking could be just the dog for you!  He is ready to be your jogging, biking, & hiking buddy.  He has a high prey drive and is always on the lookout for those pesky gophers and scampering squirrels.  We suspect he may need a home with no small furry or feathered creatures that would need to be chased down.   If you're ready for a partner in adventure, please consider Viking!  Come check out Viking and our other dogs available for adoption at 2650 Washington Blvd, Crescent City, CA 95531.

animal.description:
Animal Profile: Cher is an adorable ~5 year old Chihuahua mix who was rescued from a high kill shelter in southern CA. She will be joining us from California on January 10th.

Seattle Foster Update: Meet Cher! She is a sweet, timid at times, and adorable little pup. She takes a couple of days to warm up but once she does, she follows you all around. Her favorite activity is lounging with her pack, cuddled in a blanket on a couch or a bed. She loves belly rubs. She is potty trained and has not had an accident in the home as long as she has been on a consistent potty routine. Generally quiet, she gets excited when invited to play and does bark a bit, which can be trained out of her. She gets excited around other dogs, wanting to play with them (in the process may bark). She is crate-trained. She prefers sleeping in the bed with her humans but is comfortable sleeping in her crate as well. She is not very fond of toys though. She is also good with other humans (as mentioned may not immediately go into their arms but is comfortable with stranger's touch). She is also great with car rides. We take her for long rides around the town. We will continue to post more info as she settles in!

Adoption Info: Adoption fee is $500, which includes spay/neuter, current rabies/DAPPV/bordetella vaccinations, microchip, health certificate, and heartworm test. All adoption fees are donations to a Washington non-profit corporation and all donations go to benefit the animals in our rescue.

Apply online at www.DogGoneSeattle.org

Animal History: This dog was rescued from euthanasia at a high-kill shelter in California and will be available for adoption in Seattle, once evaluated in a loving foster home in the greater Seattle area.

animal.description:
I’ve been in and out of the pound since I was a pup, but that hasn’t stopped me from being the most loving, sweetest, cuddliest and happiest good girl out there! I’ve kept my puppy energy after all these years and love hiking, going on long walks and even going for runs with my person. I’d prefer to be in a home where I’m your one-and-only companion animal (so I can get all the cuddles!), but love the dog park as long as there aren’t any smaller pups around. It’s not that I don’t like them and want to get to meet them, it’s just that I’m not as gentle around lil’s when we have disagreements… I don’t want to get blamed when they pick the fight. Similarly, I don’t want to be blamed for knocking over a small child, so I would say I make a better playmate for teenagers.

If you are interested in meeting this pooch, please download the Adoption Questionnaire (farescue.org/pdf_files/questionnaire_canine.pdf), fill it out and email it back to us at info@farescue.org or fax (310) 362-0321. You can also meet this and/or other available dogs at our weekend adoptions.

[Kali is 5 years old and weighs 68 lbs.]

Her name is Baby, she is 2.5 years old has been spayed, is on heart worm preventative, is UTD on vaccines and is looking for a new home.  

Baby is dog selective, so for that reason we are looking for her to be adopted into a home as an only pet.  She is a very sweet girl to people and "some" dogs.  She came from an abusive home and has been very loved but just cannot get along with one of the dogs in the household.

She is house broken, crate trained and is an active dog that has a good energy level and can take all the  "play time" you can give to her.  She is leash trained, so maybe a family that would jog with her would also be helpful. 

Because of her energy level we would require a home with a fenced yard so she can freely play.  

Currently she is being fostered in North Carolina and would be transported to an approved adopter.  If you're looking for a wonderful playmate, you can find our online application at:  
http://diamonddogsrescueinc.com

animal.description:
Meet Levi! This guy is a handsome American Pit Bull Terrier mix who is looking for his forever home.

This shy boy has a very sad story. He came from a small town in Texas where he was dumped in a kill shelter after flooding due to a hurricane that destroyed the area. Levi found himself sick, homeless, broken down and afraid of the world, through no fault of his own. It's likely that Levi missed out on some key socialization as a puppy, and sees the world a little differently than other dogs. Levi was so broken down in a shelter environment, that he sat frozen and trembling in fear. Levi's past was unclear, but we knew for certain that he wouldn't have survived without help from a loving foster home.

Levi is 4-5 years old, 64 lbs with an athletic build. He has a shiny reverse brindle coat and large, soulful eyes. He is a mellow, quiet guy who is constantly surveying the world around him, trying to understand his place in it. Levi communicates differently than other dogs. When he is nervous or unsure, he will retreat, or freeze. He requires a structured, calm household with adults and older children where he can move slowly to learn to be comfortable. He thrives in the outdoors but takes some time getting used to new indoor environments. 

Levi is a dog that needs a very slow decompression. The key word with Levi is "baby steps" as it takes him some time to build up his confidence in new environments. He learned how to be a dog for the first time in a home and Levi's goofy, silly side started to come out as he learned how to trust, socialize and play. His previous foster family said he is an absolute snuggle monster and loves nothing more than cuddling up at his families side on the couch, sprawled out in comfort. 

Levi would do great as an only dog with an active owner who enjoys plenty of hikes, runs and walks. Although Levi has lived with dogs in the past, it has become evident he is more of an introvert when it comes to other canines. He enjoys the occasional play date romp with dog friends but prefers to come home and recharge in doggy solitude with his humans.

Levi has lived in the big city, but is a country boy at heart where he has plenty of space for hikes and to run. He is medium energy and loves to learn new tricks and excels at training, especially when treats are involved. He is very food motivated and intelligent. Levi loves the outdoors and finds joy in chasing squirrels and birds, destroying cardboard boxes. Due to his prey drive, we recommend a home without cats or other small animals. Levi is great with all humans, large and small.

The American Pit Bull Terrier is a widely misunderstood breed, often thought of as protection or guardian animal. Levi is the opposite. He is not protective, but shy and gentle. He is easy on a leash and has grown accustomed to sleeping on the couch while he people are hanging out at home, and would enjoy sleeping in bed with you at night, if you eased him into it. Levi is neutered, potty trained, crate trained, UTD on all vaccines, micro-chipped and heartworm free.

To apply for Levi please fill out an application at www.doggedly.org/adoption-app

Mac was rescued from a high kill shelter in North Carolina.  Taken to the shelter as an intentional stray, he was out of time and next to be euthanized when we saw his smiling face and made arrangements to have him pulled for our rescue.

He was fully vetted, neutered, microchipped and quarantined before sending to foster.  He is currently in NH looking to find his forever family.

His foster mom says: This handsome boy needs a home! Lots of energy and he's a huge snuggle bug. Hes great with kids and other dogs. Loves car rides, walks, kisses, and lots of love.  He needs some training on leash, we've been working on that one.   

Around 2.5 years old, Mack is a retriever/hound mix weighing in at 61 lbs. 
Trainer evaluation available and he said:
Mack FULL of energy, loves people other dogs and treats. This energy is all friendly and happy wanting to play active. Mack is one of the happiest dogs I have ever evaluated.  Because of his good energy level we will require that he go to a home that is active and where there is a fenced in yard so he can get good exercise 

He is good with other dogs...very playful and friendly...BUT no cats.

animal.description:
Meet Teddy!
He is a 2 year-old shar-pei pitbull mix weighing in around 55 pounds. He is housebroken, potty trained, gentle on a leash, and is a low energy boy. He is currently in a foster home with children, other dogs, and pet rats and does well with all of them! Teddy is currently in training with KISS dog training working on his fearfulness, but once he learns to trust you, he loves with all of his heart. His foster mom says he is extremely loyal and she loves him to death! KISS has offered a free 30 minute consult with Teddy's new adopters to continue his training. Teddy was neglected as a pup, so he needs a loyal family that is willing to learn all that they can about him and dogs in general. He will make a family extremely happy!

If you are interested in meeting Teddy, please fill out an application via our website at https://therescueproject.net/adoption-application and we will get back to you via email once your application has been reviewed.  If you have further questions please feel free to reach out to us at adoptionstrp@gmail.com

Teddy's adoption fee is $200 and includes age appropriate vaccines, spay/neuter, microchip, deworm, heartworm testing.

She arrived at the shelter a diamond in the rough~ her coat was matted and neglected and her eye needed to be removed. She got a totally 80's new wave haircut to save some hair around her face when she was groomed prior to her surgery. Arleen sees fine out of her remaining eye and has no trouble getting around the house and likes to explore in the yard. She is gentle and sweet and gets along well with other dogs. She has a good hearty appetite and gets excited when you come home or its time for her to eat. She will make a nice little companion dog for someone looking for a little buddy happy just to be close to you. Arleen is house and crate trained and will use a pee pad if you put one out for her. Arleen is the sweetest little lady who deserves to be spoiled and loved in her golden years. Her adoption fee is $200.

Please fill out a pre-adoption application so we know you are interested in meeting/adopting one of our animals.
The breeds of our dogs and cats are a 'best guess.' We often do not know what mix they are and have to base it on what we think they look like, and base it on breeds often found in the area they came from. Most of our dogs who have gotten DNA tests done are 4-10 breeds mixed together. Because their breed mix is a guess we cannot guarantee a 'full grown size' of many of our younger animals.Interested in adopting me? Click here to fill out an application!Happy Tails Rescue Minnesota is located at 7940 University Ave NE, Fridley MN 55432. We are open for adoption events from 12-5 every Sunday. If there is a certain animal you want to meet at one the events please fill out a preadoption application to directly contact their foster family or check our Facebook page to see if they will be there! Their event attendance is based on the availability of their foster family.
Home visits (video tours or in person) are required for all dog adoptions. All of our cats and dogs are INDOOR pets and are NOT to be left outside unattended (even in a fenced yard), or running loose!

animal.description:
Hi! I'm Burke and I'm ~45 lbs of love. My favorite thing in the world is to be pet by my foster humans. I do entertain myself by chewing on bones and playing with toys, but I'd trade them for cuddles on the couch any day! When I'm really happy, I wag my little tail so fast and my whole bottom wiggles! Maybe I can show you sometime!

I have two foster dog siblings right now. One is full grown like me and we love to run around outside and chase each other. My other foster sibling is a little puppy. I was pretty scared of her at first, but I'm quickly warming up to her! I was actually a bit scared of a few things when I first got here (why are LaCroix's so loud when they open, and why does my human drink so many???) but I'm gaining confidence so fast.

At night I sleep in my crate next to the puppy. I'd definitely prefer to sleep in my crate in the same room as my people, or maybe even in bed with them! Have I mentioned I love humans?

My perfect forever family will be affectionate, while still providing me structure & guidance. I'd love to take a training class and learn the commands that my foster sister gets all these treats for - I like treats so I'll learn quickly! I'd also love to have a dog sibling to keep me company, and continue to build my confidence!



--------------------------------------------



All our Warrior Dogs will have all age appropriate medical care and vaccines, a microchip, and spay/neuter before adoption unless age is a factor with a puppy younger than 6-12 months at the time of adoption. If that is the case, the spay/neuter will be covered in the adoption fee and the owner will be responsible to have the procedure completed at a Warrior Dog Rescue Veterinarian at the appropriate time.

Please note that the majority of our dogs in rescue are from shelters where they have been found as strays or abandoned. Their breed description is based on our very best educated guess based on physical characteristics and their dispositions. If they came to our rescue as an owner surrender, the breed description will be listed as provided by the previous owner.

Adoption Fee - $450

To apply for this pup, please submit an Adoption Application at http://warriordogrescue.com/adopt/adoption-application/

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.MEDICAL HOLDFrom Major's rescue angel: It was painfully obvious from the get go that this poor boy had been abused and neglected for a long time. Major flinched any time I tried to pet him. He ran away when I got near him. He was scared, confused, hungry, dirty and in pain. I gave him a nice meal and lots of water, which he scarfed down. I then watched as he went to the bathroom, in extreme pain. Before trying anything further, I allowed him to decompress safely inside his kennel. After about 30 minutes of barking, he finally wore himself out and took a good 4 hour nap. Once he woke up, I gave him a nice warm bath. During the bath, he kept drinking all the water and just looking at me confused--like 'what is this lady doing?? She is giving me nice touches and massaging my whole body?? This is weird, but I think I like it.'In giving Major a bath, I was able to fully exam his body and realize the extent of his medical issues. It was heartbreaking. He was in such pain while pooping because he had a perineal hernia the size of a grapefruit! He also had a 5 pound pendulum tumor hanging from his side. I could easily count at least a dozen more tumors/masses over his body. I also learned his tongue hangs out because the inside of his mouth is completely jacked up!

In less than 12 hours, Major has already begun trusting me. During breakfast, his butt never stopped wiggling and he wanted me to pet him the whole time while eating. Every time I stopped, he would turn around and look at me like I was a dumb-dumb for stopping! After breakfast, he just wanted to sit by me and lick my face! When I put him back in his kennel, he immediately just laid down and started sawing logs He now feels safe and knows life is going to be pretty okay from now on. There is no better feeling than this.

animal.description:
Gonzo is an adorable blond 5 year old Lhasa Apso, who weighs about 15 pounds.  He is looking for an understanding home where he can snuggle and love and be cared for on his own terms.  Those terms are generous, but they are specific, so potential adopters should read his bio carefully before applying to adopt him.

Gonzo was found as a stray and spent some time in the doggy jail before Wonder Pets was asked to help him out by getting him into a foster home and loving on him.  

Gonzo was found to have significant dry eye issues, and it quickly became clear that he is very picky about how his eyes are cared for.  Gonzo has severe anxiety about having  eye drops administered and is extremely uncooperative.  His foster family has worked through a care regimen with eventual wonderful success and his eyes are showing huge improvement.  Any adopter will need to commit to continued lifetime care of his dry eye and understand potential future complications and costs of this condition.  Techniques that worked (and didn't work) to encourage his cooperation will be provided to potential adopters. 

Gonzo is cooperative for most routine care, but does NOT cooperate well with common grooming of his face (such as trimming of his facial hair).  He will usually allow a trusted person to brush him, but is very uncooperative for grooming that would require restraining.  Potential adopters should be aware of this and be able to recognize dog body language and help him navigate stressful grooming care.  Adopters should understand that it will take time and patience for him to build up trust for this, and should be committed to working with him long-term to build this trust to work through some of these issues. 

Because Gonzo is very picky about the way he is physically interacted with (especially around his face), he would NOT be a good fit for young children living in the home.  Older resident children that are good at understanding and respecting dog boundaries would be fine, but a monitored introduction would be required prior to adoption.  Visiting respectful children (with supervision) would likely be fine for Gonzo. 
As Gonzo has grown in trust with his foster family, his playful and affectionate nature has become apparent.  Gonzo loves to snuggle , preferring snuggles on the bed at night over sleeping in his kennel.  Gonzo also loves to play on occasion and enjoys a squeaker toy and maybe some games of chase. 

Gonzo appears to be potty trained, but a new home may require some work at re-learning what he already knows.  After a transitional period, he is generally pretty good about pottying where he should go. 
Gonzo loves to go for walks and will happily dance and throw himself excitedly into his harness at walk times!  He enjoys and needs these walks so much, but does not require a lot of exercise.  He enjoys meeting most new people (he does prefer women, but will warm up to most men) and other respectful dogs of all sizes, and is perfect with his resident foster cat.  Gonzo would not be a good fit for a resident dog that is bossy or forceful with him, as he will react negatively to being bullied by another dog.  

When Gonzo is feeling silly, he will attempt to dart out a door trying to entice his people into a game of chase.  Potential adopters should have a plan in place to keep him safe from the dangers of this behavior!  Gonzo is affectionate and enjoys being with his people, but like many Lhasa Apsos, he is stubborn and prefers to obey requests on his own terms.  Patience is a must with this boy!

Gonzo does not like to be left by his people and will vocalize that displeasure loud and long at times.  He will not be a good fit for apartments or close-dwelling living situations.  He would prefer a family that is home more often than not, or that is able to bring him with them on family outings/working outside the home setting.  He rides well in the car and will wait patiently while his people are running errands.  Gonzo's foster family is currently working from home, but he has been able to be left for several hours while they are away and has tolerated this okay.  

Gonzo is neutered, microchipped, wormed, and current on routine and rabies vaccinations.  His adoption donation is $450.

No phone calls please, go to www.wonderpetsrescue.petfinder.com to complete an adoption application.  Wonder Pets Rescue is a 501c3 non-profit organization and adoption donations are tax deductible.  Like us on Facebook, www.facebook.com/wonderpetsrescue.

animal.description:
Meet Ruby, a precious one-year-old, 45 lb. boxer mix ready. This sweet girl has not had a very good start to her life. She was found as a stray on the streets of North Carolina with a piece of metal chain around her neck. It was clear from her timid personality, and scars, that she endured neglect from her previous owners. Now that she is in a loving foster home in Connecticut, she is starting to warm up and show her true personality.

Once she's comfortable, Ruby LOVES to cuddle and will happily give you kisses. Her tail will wag happily as she takes treats gently from your hand and she is beginning to roll over for belly rubs. She enjoys the company of her humans, along with other dogs. Her foster family says she has great manners, is housetrained, and walks very well on leash. She needs an adopter that is willing to take it slow with her and one whom understands decompression time with rescue dogs. This dog has been through a lot and just wants love. A fenced yard is highly preferred.

Her adoption fee is $350 and Ruby comes up to date on vaccines, microchipped, heartworm negative, and will be spayed soon (appointment is scheduled for 2/16). If you are interested in adopting this sweet girl, please complete the application at form.jotform.com/200883908893166 or email info@happilyfureverafter.org.

animal.description:
Hello everyone! My name is Rico! I have an extremely heart breaking story. I am a 10 year old chihuahua. I am around 6 pounds and my life hasn’t always been easy. I have always lived with my former owner until she overdosed on drugs. I was found locked in her room with her deceased body after 4 days by EMTs. When they found me I was so hungry and so thirsty. A family member came right over to pick me up but they couldn’t care for me long term so a pals volunteer came to get me at 12:30 in the morning. She said I am such a very good boy, I am great with all of her dogs of all shapes and sizes and I am even good with her cat, she is working on me to let her hold me but for now I’m happy just being close to her and wagging my tail every time she says my name. I haven’t always had a great life and even though I had one owner my whole life I didn’t really do much with me, I was kind of left to fend for myself. I am a very sweet boy who is learning all of the new rules and how to be a dog that is loved. She doesn’t kennel me when she leaves and I’m a very good boy when she is gone. I would love a home where I can get used to somebody and never have to be moved again.

The adoption donation fee is $300 which is tax-deductible and goes towards the care of homeless pets with Pals for Paws. 

To expedite the adoption process you can fill out an application online at www.palsforpawsinc.com/adopt. Please note the adoption application doesn’t bind you to anything. Pals for Paws reserves the right to refuse any adoption application for any reason and at any point in the adoption process. 

To view our other wonderful Homeless Pets visit www.palsforpawsinc.com/pet-list ALSO be sure to LIKE Pals for Paws on Facebook at www.facebook.com/palsforpaws.inc 

All Pals for Paws Rescue animals are fully vetted:
*Spayed/Neutered
*Groomed
*Shots updated plus Leptospirosis 
*Micro-chipped
*Dewormed 
*On Heart-worm prevention
*On Flea and Tick Prevention
* Dentals are done if needed 

You only need to see your vet for a “meet n greet” of your new family member and to turn in their medical records.

Pals for Paws is a 501(c)3 animal rescue. Every penny donated and every penny received through adoption fees goes right back into the organization. There are times when the volunteers have to dip into their pockets to help the animals. We do not euthanize because a pet is sick, heart-worm positive, or has a broken leg; we fix it all, big and small. We strive to go above and beyond when caring for and socializing our animals. We understand the importance of getting to know each and every animal available for adoption in an effort to place them in the most perfect home possible. 
If you are looking for a particular type of dog or have special needs, We can help! Contact us at www.palsforpawsinc.com

animal.description:
FUREVER HOME NEEDED! Please share! Help find this guy the loving home he deserves. #ADOPTDART 

Ya see, life hasn’t been kind to him. His eyes and scars tell a story none of us can imagine. Someone failed this guy, someone tortured him, someone broke him. Dart was found astray in Texas and ended up in the Harris county shelter. Tucked in a corner shaking he wasted away, he lost all hope, he was out of time. We couldn’t let that happen! Rescue Rehome Repeat of South Louisiana has given this sweet boy the second chance he so deserves. Dart has been in our program 2.5 months now. His foster mom has been committed to his care and rehabilitation filling his life with love he’s never felt before. LOVE! That’s the key word. Gentle pets, warm beds, meals, treats and everything a dog needs. He’s coming around! He has still yet to make a sound (no barks, no whines, no growls, no anything). He still prefers to be tucked away in a corner to feel safe and secure, but loves to go for a walk with his humans. He also loves his foster brothers and sisters. He’s welcoming to all humans, kids (loved his new baby human although he wasn’t uncertain about the crying) and doggos though he much prefers a quiet room to himself. He hasn’t quite learned to be a normal dog yet. Dart doesn’t run, he doesn’t jump, beg, get the zoomies, fetch, play ball or even eat in your presence. He’s just kind of “there”. But boy, if someone has a big heart, I promise you just some more TLC and this sweet pup is going to soar!
Dart is seeking someone compassionate and patient. Someone who well help him relax, trust, and learn to be a pup. Honestly, he’s just seeking LOVE!

I know the RIGHT home for him is out there! Please share his story, please share his face. Someone out there is going to love you buddy, I PROMISE!!

animal.description:
Please contact JoEllen (sagdinfo@aol.com) for more information about this pet.Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

** This dog is in a foster home in San Antonio, TX. Prospective adopters must be able to travel to San Antonio to complete the adoption process. Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/ **
Wyatt is an adorable 3-month-old Retriever blend who weighs approximately 10.6 pounds. He has a sweet temperament and is active and playful. He will make a loyal companion.
Please understand you are committing to providing a good home for his entire life (up to 15+ years or more) - not just until his puppy cuteness wears off.
You must be committed to housebreaking, age-appropriate enrichment and exercise, leash training, grooming needs, and positive socialization. Like most puppies, he may chew on anything within his reach to include but not limited to baseboards, shoes, socks, children's toys, electrical cords, plants, etc.
His adoption fee is $300. This includes his neuter surgery, rabies vaccination, Nobivac Canine 1-DAPP vaccinations, Bravecto, Drontal Plus, Tri-Heart Plus Chewable Tablet, 24PetWatch microchip, leash and collar, and a trial offer for 24PetWatch Pet Insurance.
Please be aware that puppies and small breed dogs do get adopted quickly so interested parties are encouraged to apply online at www.saspca.org.
Please ensure your application is complete before submitting. We do verify property ownership, landlord references, apartment/HOA restrictions, veterinary references, and criminal histories.
Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio TX 78232. Event hours are 11:00 a.m. to 3:00 p.m.
Additional questions may be directed to sagdinfo@gmail.com.
** This dog is in a foster home in San Antonio, TX. Prospective adopters must be able to travel to San Antonio to complete the adoption process. Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/ **

- IMPORTANT INFORMATION -

SASPCA Homeward Bound Dog Rescue and San Antonio Great Dane Rescue are 501(c)(3) foster-based rescue groups based in San Antonio, Texas.

Our group focuses on assisting open admission shelters in South Texas where over 32,000 dogs and cats are euthanized each year.

Our puppies and dogs are completely vetted and live in foster homes. They are spayed/neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, dewormed, and tested for heartworm disease.All adoptions include one month of flea and heartworm preventative, leash and collar, and opportunity to enroll in a 30-day trial of pet insurance.

Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio, TX 78232. Event hours are typically 11:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m.

We also host additional adoption events throughout the year. Please visit our Facebook pages for the most current event schedules.

https://m.facebook.com/HomewardBoundDogRescue/?tsid=0.11494693985281179&source=typeahead

https://m.facebook.com/profile.php?id=185497084826453&tsid=0.7626298417270982&source=typeahead

If your adoption application is approved and you are traveling from out-of-town, we hold your chosen pet for one hour past the event start time to allow for travel time.

We are an all-volunteer organization and do not currently have the resources to process out-of-state adoptions.

Our puppies, purebred dogs, and small breed dogs do get adopted quickly so we encourage interested parties to apply online.

Please apply here:

http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

animal.description:
Mugsy is a handsome, senior, male, tan chihuahua with a date of birth of 8/21/11. His owner was no longer able to keep he and Sasha’s so they found themselves in need of rescue. Even though they both came from the same household they do not appear to be a bonded pair. Mugsy is a total sweetheart. He is neutered, up to date on vaccinations and being kept on heartworm and flea and tick prevention to maintain his good health. Mugsy has a throat condition that requires medication twice a day. Due to his more delicate nature, he will not be considered for homes with children. He will be a loving companion for someone in a quiet home. Mugsy’s adoption donation is $225. If you would like to adopt Mugsy please complete the first step in the adoption process by filling out our online adoption application. You can find the link to our on-line adoption application at www.arfarkansas.com on the right-hand side of our home page. An application does not obligate you to adopt from us, but it does show that you are serious about the adoption process. Please remember our organization is staffed completely by volunteers.
Please Note: All applications are processed in the order received, but an adoption is made to the best application received for each of our animals. All applicants must provide a vet reference on the adoption application. If you are adopting a dog from ARFA, a fenced in yard for the dog will be required. Home visits often occur with each adoption. ARFA has the right to deny adoption to any applicant for any reason without explanation. Please remember that the adoption donation is not for purchase of a dog, but rather to cover the medical cost of all dogs in our care.
THE FINE PRINT
1.  Animal Rescue Fund Arkansas reserves the right to deny any application, for any reason without explanation to the applicant.
2.  You understand that we often take many applications on the same animal and that they are processed in the order that they come in. An application is in no way a reservation for any animal or a guarantee that you will be selected to adopt the animal.
3.  If your application Is approved, you will be asked to sign a separate adoption contract.
4.  Once the trial period is over, usually 1 week unless there are special circumstances, the adoption donation cannot be returned to you for any reason. It will have been used to help rescue another homeless animal and is no longer available therefore, if you return the dog to us for any reason, you will not be refunded your donation.
5.  If the animal you want to adopt is placed in another home, you can transfer your application to another A.R.F.A. animal without completing additional paperwork.
6.  You understand that this is a rescued pet. We rarely have any information about their past life circumstances.  We have all animals examined by a vet, brought up to date on shots, given their rabies vaccine, spayed/neutered (If old enough), wormed and checked for heartworms and if positive begin treatment.  We do our best to ensure that we are placing healthy pets but can make no guarantee to the health or temperament of this pet, and vet expenses are the responsibility of the adoptive family from the date of the adoption.  We require that you take the pet to a vet within one week of adoption for a check-up and to allow your vet to get a baseline for your new pet’s health.

animal.description:
These 6 puppies are from Angel's litter. They are 7 weeks old and will be coming to FL on 2/10/21. They will need to be fostered in pairs of 2 until they get their 2nd set of shots when 11 weeks old. At that time, they can be officially adopted. There are 5 boys and 1 girl, noted on their pics. below. Mama Angel will also need a separate foster when she comes on 2/10/21. She's a heeler mix and is very loving and good with other dogs; cats unknown. The father of the litter is unknown. From the looks of the puppies, it looks like they could have some shepherd in them and will be medium to larger in size when grown. Although we never know and there is no guarantee, we estimate size to be 40-50 lbs. when grown. Since these are young puppies, we aren't adopting to homes where people are gone for a large portion of the day and the dogs will be left unattended. People with like energy dogs and prior puppy parents are given preference as well. These puppies will also need proper socialization and training so please be mindful of this when applying and be committed to providing this.

To apply to foster-to-adopt:
https://www.ewenityfarmsbch.com/forms/form?formid=5924.

To apply to foster (no intent to adopt):

animal.description:
Hi! This is Zeus. He is a one year old Belgian malinois/lab mix. He is a total cuddle bug and loves to give kisses! He is crate/ house trained. He loves being outside but gets distracted easily on walks and will pull for the first few minutes. I feel that he thrive and do best in a home without small children due to the fact that my toddler stresses him out with sudden movements/ loud noises etc. He has never shown signs of aggression. He is up to date on vaccinations and neutered! 

Behaviors: 

skittish with loud noises/startled easily
Has separation anxiety (will cry when crated but only ever crated if I leave. I work from home so I only leave to grab my daughter from daycare or grab groceries) 
Will dig if not exercised enough
Has generalized anxiety/trouble sitting still but this is improving. 


Zeus is being rehomed. Zeus needs training and consistency in his life.

animal.description:
Hello everyone! My name is Alfie! I’m a one year old shih tzu yorkie mix and I am so small and sweet and cute! I am a little superstar and as sweet as it gets. Everyone who meets me loves me! I am house snd crate trained! 

The adoption donation fee is $500 which is tax-deductible and goes towards the care of homeless pets with Pals for Paws. 

To expedite the adoption process you can fill out an application online at www.palsforpawsinc.com/adopt. Please note the adoption application doesn’t bind you to anything. Pals for Paws reserves the right to refuse any adoption application for any reason and at any point in the adoption process. 

To view our other wonderful Homeless Pets visit www.palsforpawsinc.com/pet-list ALSO be sure to LIKE Pals for Paws on Facebook at www.facebook.com/palsforpaws.inc 

All Pals for Paws Rescue animals are fully vetted:
*Spayed/Neutered
*Groomed
*Shots updated plus Leptospirosis 
*Micro-chipped
*Dewormed 
*On Heart-worm prevention
*On Flea and Tick Prevention
* Dentals are done if needed 

You only need to see your vet for a “meet n greet” of your new family member and to turn in their medical records.

Pals for Paws is a 501(c)3 animal rescue. Every penny donated and every penny received through adoption fees goes right back into the organization. There are times when the volunteers have to dip into their pockets to help the animals. We do not euthanize because a pet is sick, heart-worm positive, or has a broken leg; we fix it all, big and small. We strive to go above and beyond when caring for and socializing our animals. We understand the importance of getting to know each and every animal available for adoption in an effort to place them in the most perfect home possible. 
If you are looking for a particular type of dog or have special needs, We can help! Contact us at www.palsforpawsinc.com

animal.description:
Penny Sweetiepie. This could be Penny’s middle name. Yep, Ms Penny is as sweet as pie <3 

Penny is as perfect as they come. She is like your canine 'jack of all trades’. She could be your running and hiking partner and after all that is done with, she could be your bestest cuddle buddy. Netflix night? Penny is all in for a couple of hours of cuddles! Penny is very much about her humans. When indoors, she is content just being close to and hanging out with her humans but show her a huge yard or field and she is gonnnnnne! She will run like the wind! There will be no catching up to her. Now, if you have high value treats handy, that may do the trick…. Penny loves to chase ball and chew toys. If you have things going on, Penny will take the hint and quietly do her thing. She will check in every now and then to make sure you are staying on track with your chores. If Ms Penny is displeased about something, you will hear about it. She will grumble and give you her 2 cents :D 

Penny is 12-18 months old, 50lb Bluetick Coonhound. She is looking for an active home that could provide her with the mental and physical stimulation that she needs as well as valuable family time. Human and furry siblings are welcome!

animal.description:
Please contact JoEllen (sagdinfo@aol.com) for more information about this pet.Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

** This dog is in a foster home in San Antonio, TX. Prospective adopters must be able to travel to San Antonio to complete the adoption process. Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/ **
Jackson is an adorable 3-month-old Blue Heeler blend who weighs approximately 5.3 pounds. Jackson initially is shy but once you offer him treats, he quickly displays his affectionate and playful nature. His ideal owner should have experience with herding breeds as they often can require extra training and exercise than more sedentary breeds.
Please understand you are committing to providing a good home for his entire life (up to 15+ years or more) - not just until his puppy cuteness wears off.
You must be committed to housebreaking, age-appropriate enrichment and exercise, leash training, grooming needs, and positive socialization. Like most puppies, he may chew on anything within his reach to include but not limited to baseboards, shoes, socks, children's toys, electrical cords, plants, etc.
His adoption fee is $300. This includes his neuter surgery, rabies vaccination, Nobivac Canine 1-DAPP vaccinations, Bravecto, Drontal Plus, Tri-Heart Plus Chewable Tablet, 24PetWatch microchip, leash and collar, and a trial offer for 24PetWatch Pet Insurance.
Please be aware that puppies and small breed dogs do get adopted quickly so interested parties are encouraged to apply online at www.saspca.org.
Please ensure your application is complete before submitting. We do verify property ownership, landlord references, apartment/HOA restrictions, veterinary references, and criminal histories.
Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio TX 78232. Event hours are 11:00 a.m. to 3:00 p.m.
Additional questions may be directed to sagdinfo@gmail.com.
** This dog is in a foster home in San Antonio, TX. Prospective adopters must be able to travel to San Antonio to complete the adoption process. Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/ **

- IMPORTANT INFORMATION -

SASPCA Homeward Bound Dog Rescue and San Antonio Great Dane Rescue are 501(c)(3) foster-based rescue groups based in San Antonio, Texas.

Our group focuses on assisting open admission shelters in South Texas where over 32,000 dogs and cats are euthanized each year.

Our puppies and dogs are completely vetted and live in foster homes. They are spayed/neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, dewormed, and tested for heartworm disease.All adoptions include one month of flea and heartworm preventative, leash and collar, and opportunity to enroll in a 30-day trial of pet insurance.

Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio, TX 78232. Event hours are typically 11:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m.

We also host additional adoption events throughout the year. Please visit our Facebook pages for the most current event schedules.

https://m.facebook.com/HomewardBoundDogRescue/?tsid=0.11494693985281179&source=typeahead

https://m.facebook.com/profile.php?id=185497084826453&tsid=0.7626298417270982&source=typeahead

If your adoption application is approved and you are traveling from out-of-town, we hold your chosen pet for one hour past the event start time to allow for travel time.

We are an all-volunteer organization and do not currently have the resources to process out-of-state adoptions.

Our puppies, purebred dogs, and small breed dogs do get adopted quickly so we encourage interested parties to apply online.

Please apply here:

http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

animal.description:
Male, 2 years, pit bull X, 65 lbs

Meet Berry, aka Bear.  He has had a rough start to life in Canada and as such he needs a foster/adopter to help him work with his trust issues.  He loves men and will follow them to the ends of the earth.  Women and kids he has a hard time trusting and it takes time, a lot of treats and proper introductions.  As such, since his trust issues include kids, we are recommending a home with no children.  He loves going for walks and runs, but no off leash for this beauty because of his lack of trusting strangers. Once trust is built, he is amazing and will play and snuggle all day.

Our rescue is called BARCS. We are a registered Non Profit.
Our Website is www.barcsrescue.com. All our animals are posted on the website and updated often. If you would like to proceed we need an adoption application to be filled out. They can be found on our website. Once we receive your application, we will contact you to arrange a meeting with the pup you are interested in. 
We look forward to hearing from you

animal.description: Daisy Mae is looking for her forever home. Daisy is a sweet spayed female chi cross. She is about 2 years old. A long legged beauty, she weighs about 10 pounds. A stray from the Rio Grande Valley in south Texas, she was rescued and sent up to Montana to find a home. Daisy is house trained, doesn't stray far when outside, and loves the security of a kennel, provided the door is left open! As is typical of chi's, Daisy is shy at first, but given her space and time, she warms up and wants to be with her person/people all the time. She does the cutest little tap dance when she sees you and wants your attention. She would do best in a home with other dogs, as she is more comfortable in general if there are dogs around. She gets along with other dogs and is fine with cats. She does like to sleep with her people and loves to hang out and cuddle on the couch. If you are that special home that she is looking for, please fill out an online adoption application on our website LSAR.org

These 6 puppies are from Angel's litter. They are 7 weeks old and will be coming to FL on 2/10/21. They will need to be fostered in pairs of 2 until they get their 2nd set of shots when 11 weeks old. At that time, they can be officially adopted. There are 5 boys and 1 girl, noted on their pics. below. Mama Angel will also need a separate foster when she comes on 2/10/21. She's a heeler mix and is very loving and good with other dogs; cats unknown. The father of the litter is unknown. From the looks of the puppies, it looks like they could have some shepherd in them and will be medium to larger in size when grown. Although we never know and there is no guarantee, we estimate size to be 40-50 lbs. when grown. Since these are young puppies, we aren't adopting to homes where people are gone for a large portion of the day and the dogs will be left unattended. People with like energy dogs and prior puppy parents are given preference as well. These puppies will also need proper socialization and training so please be mindful of this when applying and be committed to providing this.

To apply to foster-to-adopt:
https://www.ewenityfarmsbch.com/forms/form?formid=5924.

animal.description:
Female, 3 years, German shepherd/Boxer X, 71 lbs

My name is Nala. I am looking for my forever home. I am extremely loving and I want to please you. I am smart and do not miss very much. I love exercise and would love a fenced backyard. I also love walks but I do pull a bit. I'm working on that though. I am living in a house that is quite busy. I have two older sisters and a 10-year-old brother. I get along with them quite well. I know how to use the bathroom outside but I have had a couple accidents inside my new foster mom's house. I haven't been around other dogs so I'm not sure how I would act. I know when I see other pups through the window or on my walks, I start wagging my tail and get very excited. I know how to go into my kennel and I sleep through the night. I’m also not much of a barker but get quite excited if I see a squirrel through the window.  I love to be surrounded by people. I can't wait to meet my new family. 

Our rescue is called BARCS. We are a registered Non Profit.
Our Website is www.barcsrescue.com. All our animals are posted on the website and updated often. If you would like to proceed we need an adoption application to be filled out. They can be found on our website. Once we receive your application, we will contact you to arrange a meeting with the pup you are interested in. 
We look forward to hearing from you

animal.description:
Hello everyone! My name is Sebastian and I am so sweet! I am an 8 month old lab mix puppy and I love everybody and everything! I am house and crate trained and as sweet as it gets! 

The adoption donation fee is $400 which is tax-deductible and goes towards the care of homeless pets with Pals for Paws. 

To expedite the adoption process you can fill out an application online at www.palsforpawsinc.com/adopt. Please note the adoption application doesn’t bind you to anything. Pals for Paws reserves the right to refuse any adoption application for any reason and at any point in the adoption process. 

To view our other wonderful Homeless Pets visit www.palsforpawsinc.com/pet-list ALSO be sure to LIKE Pals for Paws on Facebook at www.facebook.com/palsforpaws.inc 

All Pals for Paws Rescue animals are fully vetted:
*Spayed/Neutered
*Groomed
*Shots updated plus Leptospirosis 
*Micro-chipped
*Dewormed 
*On Heart-worm prevention
*On Flea and Tick Prevention
* Dentals are done if needed 

You only need to see your vet for a “meet n greet” of your new family member and to turn in their medical records.

Pals for Paws is a 501(c)3 animal rescue. Every penny donated and every penny received through adoption fees goes right back into the organization. There are times when the volunteers have to dip into their pockets to help the animals. We do not euthanize because a pet is sick, heart-worm positive, or has a broken leg; we fix it all, big and small. We strive to go above and beyond when caring for and socializing our animals. We understand the importance of getting to know each and every animal available for adoption in an effort to place them in the most perfect home possible. 
If you are looking for a particular type of dog or have special needs, We can help! Contact us at www.palsforpawsinc.com
