animal.description:
Please contact JoEllen (sagdinfo@aol.com) for more information about this pet.Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

** This dog is in a foster home in San Antonio, TX. Prospective adopters must be able to travel to San Antonio to complete the adoption process. Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/ **
Jack is an adorable 3-month-old Blue Heeler blend who weighs approximately 4.1 pounds. Jack initially is shy but once you offer him treats, he quickly displays his affectionate and playful nature. His ideal owner should have experience with herding breeds as they often can require extra training and exercise than more sedentary breeds.
Please understand you are committing to providing a good home for his entire life (up to 15+ years or more) - not just until his puppy cuteness wears off.
You must be committed to housebreaking, age-appropriate enrichment and exercise, leash training, grooming needs, and positive socialization. Like most puppies, he may chew on anything within his reach to include but not limited to baseboards, shoes, socks, children's toys, electrical cords, plants, etc.
His adoption fee is $300. This includes his neuter surgery, rabies vaccination, Nobivac Canine 1-DAPP vaccinations, Bravecto, Drontal Plus, Tri-Heart Plus Chewable Tablet, 24PetWatch microchip, leash and collar, and a trial offer for 24PetWatch Pet Insurance.
Please be aware that puppies and small breed dogs do get adopted quickly so interested parties are encouraged to apply online at www.saspca.org.
Please ensure your application is complete before submitting. We do verify property ownership, landlord references, apartment/HOA restrictions, veterinary references, and criminal histories.
Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio TX 78232. Event hours are 11:00 a.m. to 3:00 p.m.
Additional questions may be directed to sagdinfo@gmail.com.
** This dog is in a foster home in San Antonio, TX. Prospective adopters must be able to travel to San Antonio to complete the adoption process. Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/ **

- IMPORTANT INFORMATION -

SASPCA Homeward Bound Dog Rescue and San Antonio Great Dane Rescue are 501(c)(3) foster-based rescue groups based in San Antonio, Texas.

Our group focuses on assisting open admission shelters in South Texas where over 32,000 dogs and cats are euthanized each year.

Our puppies and dogs are completely vetted and live in foster homes. They are spayed/neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, dewormed, and tested for heartworm disease.All adoptions include one month of flea and heartworm preventative, leash and collar, and opportunity to enroll in a 30-day trial of pet insurance.

Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio, TX 78232. Event hours are typically 11:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m.

We also host additional adoption events throughout the year. Please visit our Facebook pages for the most current event schedules.

https://m.facebook.com/HomewardBoundDogRescue/?tsid=0.11494693985281179&source=typeahead

https://m.facebook.com/profile.php?id=185497084826453&tsid=0.7626298417270982&source=typeahead

If your adoption application is approved and you are traveling from out-of-town, we hold your chosen pet for one hour past the event start time to allow for travel time.

We are an all-volunteer organization and do not currently have the resources to process out-of-state adoptions.

Our puppies, purebred dogs, and small breed dogs do get adopted quickly so we encourage interested parties to apply online.

Please apply here:

http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

animal.description:
Available: Now
Age: 2 years
Size: Medium (35-40lbs)
Energy: Moderate
Gender: Female
Breed: Terrier/Shepherd X
Notes: Sweet and Playful

Adoption fee: $375 (view what’s included at www.manitobaunderdogs.org/adoptionfees)

Hi there, I’m Maisel! I’m a sweet young lady who came into the care of MUR for a Beat the Heat initiative, and decided to stick around! I’ve been busy getting used to the city life and now I’m ready to find a family to curl up beside.

I am currently perfecting my leash manners, but walking is one of my favourite things to do so I know that practice will make perfect for me! I am fully house trained and am working on my kennel training, but I’m so well behaved that I can be trusted loose. I live with a doggy foster sibling and enjoy their company, though sometimes I like my own space to relax. I would do best with respectful dogs and slow introductions so I can come out of my shell. That way I can be the best sister possible! I haven’t met any cats or kids yet but I’m sure with proper introductions, we could be great friends.

I’ve heard that “slow and steady wins the race” and I think the same goes for becoming best friends! I promise once I’m comfortable, I will cuddle you to your heart's content. I also make a great hand warmer for humans and will gladly trade my services for some belly rubs anytime. If we get really cozy and relaxed one day, you may just be lucky enough to hear my pig impression! My foster family says my snort is adorable and I’m pretty confident you’ll agree.

I know I’ll make a great addition to your family. Are you ready for all this extra love? Apply to meet me today!

PLEASE NOTE: Because we do not have a public shelter, an adoption application must be filled out in order to be approved to meet any of our animals available for adoption. No exceptions. Serious inquiries only.

You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.COMING SOON!

Meet sweet Buddy who is looking for a foster or forever home.

Buddy's owner had him for two years. She said she had rescued him after she found him emaciated but sadly he was living outside in a pen that he frequently escaped. About a year ago he escaped and came home with his leg injured, she brought him to the vet and they said his leg was fine how it was. Not sure of exact circumstances, but when an amazing volunteer went check on Buddy after he had been attacked by another dog, she knew he needed help immediately. He was taken to the ER where it was determined Buddy would have to have his leg amputated.

Buddy is a very sweet affectionate boy, but because of his past he would do best with female dogs only. He is getting around just fine as a new tripod and ready to start his new life as a Diamond. Please apply today to meet Buddy!

Adoption donation includes Spay/Neuter, UTD on Vaccinations, deworming, and flea treatment.

animal.description:
{s3829code380/}
If you would like to provide this dog a loving home, please fill out a pre-adoption application.

Have a question? Please read our Frequently Asked Questions and Adoption Processed Explained documentation.
_________ B I O ______________

Name:Calabaza
Size: ~Medium range: 26-60 lbs
Adoption Donation:$250 (applicable sales tax included).Adoption fees may be paid by cash or check.
Other:Spayed Female, Vaccinations current, Microchip

Calabaza is a very nice dog and is friendly with people.

Foster Home Feedback

1/23/21: A few things to know about Calabaza - she loves to pounce in the snow. She isn't afraid to take walks regardless of it being a little cold or the amount of snow outside - I assume she may be a great running buddy as well. Calabaza has been great with an energetic puppy as well as an older dog that just wants to play in spurts and have his space at other times. She sleeps like a dream and has had no accidents in the house or the kennel. She is very photogenic! Sound great? Keep reading!

Calabaza has great instincts about dogs as I stated before about being around an energetic puppy and an older dog. I would not say that Calabaza is overly energetic but she does love daily walks (sometimes begs for another with a nudge at her leash and the use of "puppy eyes"). She also loves playtime in the backyard chasing snowballs you throw! She is doing great taming a wild puppy foster right now - they have become almost instant best friends!

I would say she would do best in a house with a dog buddy or if her adopter is a single dog lady, it would be best if she isn't left for long periods of time during the day as she isn't much for the alone time. She loves space to run and does find chasing rabbits and squirrels thrilling! Calabaza sprints and pounces outside daily with the other dogs. I have about a 4-5 foot fence and she has never tried to jump up on it, but with the right motivation, she very likely could.

She is a little skittish at first, but once you have her trust, Calabaza will be all about snuggles and getting pets. She loves a good window to look out of and does bark a little, but not too much. Currently, I do kennel her while I go to work for short stints of time, but mainly because I have 3 dogs in the house and the little puppy I have here now likely wouldn't leave her alone and may chew everything! She kennels well but doesn't love it.

I do believe Calabaza would be perfectly fine to leave out during the day along with some things to keep her mind active. She does try to counter surf, so keep the buffet items to a minimum. Calabaza is definitely a special dog that loves being in a home and is learning new things every day! She can't wait to be a part of her forever home!

**
Calabaza is Lyme and Anaplasmosis positive.These are tick-borne illnesses, and she is currently being treated with Doxycycline.

To learn more about Anaplasmosis in dogs, read here: http://www.peteducation.com/article.cfm?c=2+2101&aid=3621

To learn more about Lyme disease in dogs, read here: http://www.peteducation.com/article.cfm?c=2+2102&aid=458 To view additional dogs available for adoption, please see our website: www.4luvofdog.org

animal.description:
Basic info: 
Jean-luc 
Male, Husky mix
35 pounds, though he’s working on gaining a few
No impairments, but he’s from a puppy mill and still very shy 
Yes potty trained, but still needs to go out regularly
Yes crate trained, loves his crate, it’s his safe space 
Good with other dogs, will need a doggy companion 
Not around cats but probably ok
Not around kids but he’s very skittish so 10+ is recommended
Fostered in Columbus 
Energy level: low, but hopefully medium once he’s comfortable 

Bio:
Bonjour! Meet Jean-Luc, the most handsome dog this side of France! He is an approximately 3 year old 35 pound male husky mix! 

Ok, so he’s not really from France. Jean-Luc came to speak from an awful puppy mill, with no positive human interaction. In a few weeks with his foster family, he has learned so many “dog things” like playing in the backyard with his doggy foster siblings, getting yummy treats, and sleeping on comfy beds! 

He’s such a smart boy and has picked up potty and crate training like a champ! He spends his day following his foster family around the house, though he would prefer to sit a few feet away. He’s not comfortable enough to ask for pets yet, but once he’s in his forever home, he should come out of his shell. 

Jean-Luc’s perfect home will have a fenced in yard to keep him safe, and another dog to keep him company. His future humans will need to be very patient with him as he continues to learn to be a pet. But once he’s comfortable, this sweet boy will make a lucky family very happy! Apply to meet Jean-Luc today!

If you are interested in adopting this dog, please review our adoption policies and apply online at [www.speakfortheunspoken.com/adopt](http://www.speakfortheunspoken.com/adopt).

Visit [www.speakfortheunspoken.com](http://www.speakfortheunspoken.com/) will give you more information about our rescue.

***PLEASE READ*** WE DO NOT RESPOND TO PETFINDER OR EMAIL INQUIRIES. Please fill out an application on our website if you are interested in adopting this dog. We will only set up a meeting with the dog once you have an approved adoption application. We actively manage our dogs on Petfinder, the dogs listed are available for adoption. We will remove the dog from view once they are pending adoption.

animal.description:
The arrival is planned for Feb. 27th into JFK, then transported to Raleigh. We are looking for fosters or 'foster to adopt' w/ the knowledge that the meet on Sunday may be late at night & we will have vet apts for them to keep that week! They are fully vetted. Sofi is three years old, 37 lbs. One of the teachers from the school in Mitrovica, came across Sofi & her brother Sam shortly after birth.  We think the mother was killed.  After this teacher tried. she asked if I would take them.  Sam & Sofi were with me ever since.  Sam was adopted this past summer by a special young man who just adores him.  Sofi has always been the smallest/was picked on by the other dogs in the pack here.  I keep her right next to me even inside.   She is very faithful and loving.  She is very attached to me.  She would be a great dog for a single lady.  Very easy dog!
***
Thank you for your interest in our rescues ! Events most every weekend, Saturdays, to meet some. All may be met by appointment w/ approved application. Facebook posts who will attend (current week).  Available dogs, donation button(we are non-profit) & links to adopt/volunteer www.lovemuttsrescue.org . We will email you our process & fees. When one is in "foster to adopt", they are taken off our website, but may be relisted w/in 2 weeks, if not a final adoption. Blessings, The Love Mutts Rescue Team

animal.description:
Meet  Mudflap! 

He is around 8 months to one year old.
.
This boy is very sweet and lovable as well as active and ready to get out and have fun. He is doing OK on a his leash training and on his potty training. 

Mudflap loves people, dogs, kids and cats but he is afraid of chickens! He loves to snuggle and be with his people and would love nothing more than an active family to run and hike with!

Interested in becoming a forever home for Mudflap? Fill out our online adoption application: http://www.friendswithfourpaws.org/adoption-form.html This is the first step in our process, and we don't go any further without an application.

Find more adoptable pets, news and information on Instagram @friendswithfourpaws or our Facebook page Friends with Four Paws .

We put a lot of time and energy into processing our adoptions to find our babies the best fit home for them and you.  Please do not submit an application if you are not serious about adopting Mudflap.
We are so excited to work with you to find you a new forever friend, and Mudflap the perfect forever home, and appreciate you working with us.  
For immediate consideration, please attach your application to the initial inquiry to help us expedite the process.

Our adoption fee is $525. This includes their spay/neuter surgery, full (age appropriate) vaccinations, microchip insertion and registration, deworming, heartworm testing and prevention, flea and tick prevention and travel expenses.

All of our dogs are rescued from local shelters and the general public. Each dog is then placed in a foster home where he/she is kept for quarantine, to ensure if the dog gets sick it can receive proper treatment. We have foster homes in the NJ/NY area waiting to receive their fosters. Once an animal has received an application or there's an adopter interested, we make arrangements for transport. If a dog is already in foster care in NYC/NJ, an adopter will be put in touch with the foster home AFTER an application is being processed.

Thank you in advance for your patience with our process and for making adoption YOUR option!
animal.name: Mudflap

animal.description:
The Duke of Earl is an amazing little guy. He is about 2 years old and 43 pounds, which makes him the perfect medium size. His green eyes are mesmerizing as he pays close attention to his surroundings, and his expressive eyebrows, pink nose, and fluffy tail wrap up the one of the kind package for this tender hearted guy. 

He has been in an amazing foster home and has made great strides in his socialization skills. He is fully leash and house trained and has done well with other dogs in his foster home. He is a little shy and nervous around new people, but he will trust you when given time and patience.

Earl loves snuggling on the couch, a soft bed, good food and going for walks. Most everything is a new experience for him so patience is vital. It will take time to earn his trust and affection but it's so worth the extra effort!

** This dog is in a foster home in San Antonio, TX. Prospective adopters must be able to travel to San Antonio to complete the adoption process. Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/ **
Joy is a beautiful 3-month-old Blue Heeler blend who weighs approximately 6.9 pounds. She has exquisite markings. Joy initially is shy but once your offer her treats, she quickly displays her affectionate and playful nature. Her ideal owner should have experience with herding breeds as they often can require extra training and exercise than more sedentary breeds.
Please understand you are committing to providing a good home for her entire life (up to 15+ years or more.)
You must be committed to housebreaking, age-appropriate enrichment and exercise, leash training, grooming needs, and positive socialization.
Her adoption fee is $300. This includes her spay surgery, rabies vaccination, Nobivac Canine 1-DAPP vaccination, Nobivac Intra-Trac 3 vaccination, Drontal Plus, IDEXX SNAP 4Dx Plus Test, Tri-Heart Plus chewable tablet, 24PetWatch microchip, leash and collar, and a trial offer for 24PetWatch Pet Insurance.
Please be aware that puppies and small breed dogs do get adopted quickly so interested parties are encouraged to apply online at www.saspca.org.
Please ensure your application is complete before submitting. We do verify property ownership, landlord references, apartment/HOA restrictions, veterinary references, and criminal histories.
Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio TX 78232. Event hours are 11:00 a.m. to 3:00 p.m.
Additional questions may be directed to sagdinfo@gmail.com.
** This dog is in a foster home in San Antonio, TX. Prospective adopters must be able to travel to San Antonio to complete the adoption process. Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/ **

- IMPORTANT INFORMATION -

SASPCA Homeward Bound Dog Rescue and San Antonio Great Dane Rescue are 501(c)(3) foster-based rescue groups based in San Antonio, Texas.

Our group focuses on assisting open admission shelters in South Texas where over 32,000 dogs and cats are euthanized each year.

Our puppies and dogs are completely vetted and live in foster homes. They are spayed/neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, dewormed, and tested for heartworm disease.All adoptions include one month of flea and heartworm preventative, leash and collar, and opportunity to enroll in a 30-day trial of pet insurance.

Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio, TX 78232. Event hours are typically 11:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m.

We also host additional adoption events throughout the year. Please visit our Facebook pages for the most current event schedules.

https://m.facebook.com/HomewardBoundDogRescue/?tsid=0.11494693985281179&source=typeahead

https://m.facebook.com/profile.php?id=185497084826453&tsid=0.7626298417270982&source=typeahead

If your adoption application is approved and you are traveling from out-of-town, we hold your chosen pet for one hour past the event start time to allow for travel time.

We are an all-volunteer organization and do not currently have the resources to process out-of-state adoptions.

Our puppies, purebred dogs, and small breed dogs do get adopted quickly so we encourage interested parties to apply online.

Please apply here:

http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

animal.description:
Apply to Adopt Me!

Baby is a 1-year-old sweet girl with plenty of energy. She is great with adults, children and other dogs. She is curious around cats but doesn't chase. She weighs 42 lbs. and needs a forever home where someone can spend time with her including daily exercise. She needs training to be the best girl she can be. Her foster mom is working with her on the leash, sometimes she is better than other times. Riding in the car isn't her most favorite thing to do, and does better in the car with another pup. She can be a vocal girl, ready to sound the alarm when danger is near. It seems she hasn't had a lot of toys in her life, and is learning how fun those are to play with. She loves playing with her foster mom's younger male dog. We are requiring a minimum 6-ft. fenced-in yard for her. If you live in the central Florida (Orlando) area and think you have the perfect forever home for Baby, we'd love to find out more about you. Please fill in our adoption application and we'll see if you're Baby's perfect match.

animal.description:
Sasha is a beautiful tan and white chihuahua with a date of birth of 9/26/13. She is spayed, up to date on vaccinations and being kept on heartworm and flea and tick prevention to maintain her good health. She is very loving with her foster mom but will take some time to adjust to the person that adopts her. She did not care for the stranger in the mask that came to take her pictures. Due to her fearful nature, she will not be considered for a family with children. She tolerates the other dogs in her foster home but definitely feels like she is the boss. Sasha’s adoption donation is $225. If you would like to adopt Sasha please complete the first step in the adoption process by filling out our online adoption application. You can find the link to our on-line adoption application at www.arfarkansas.com on the right-hand side of our home page. An application does not obligate you to adopt from us, but it does show that you are serious about the adoption process. Please remember our organization is staffed completely by volunteers.
Please Note: All applications are processed in the order received, but an adoption is made to the best application received for each of our animals. All applicants must provide a vet reference on the adoption application. If you are adopting a dog from ARFA, a fenced in yard for the dog will be required. Home visits often occur with each adoption. ARFA has the right to deny adoption to any applicant for any reason without explanation. Please remember that the adoption donation is not for purchase of a dog, but rather to cover the medical cost of all dogs in our care.
THE FINE PRINT
1.  Animal Rescue Fund Arkansas reserves the right to deny any application, for any reason without explanation to the applicant.
2.  You understand that we often take many applications on the same animal and that they are processed in the order that they come in. An application is in no way a reservation for any animal or a guarantee that you will be selected to adopt the animal.
3.  If your application Is approved, you will be asked to sign a separate adoption contract.
4.  Once the trial period is over, usually 1 week unless there are special circumstances, the adoption donation cannot be returned to you for any reason. It will have been used to help rescue another homeless animal and is no longer available therefore, if you return the dog to us for any reason, you will not be refunded your donation.
5.  If the animal you want to adopt is placed in another home, you can transfer your application to another A.R.F.A. animal without completing additional paperwork.
6.  You understand that this is a rescued pet. We rarely have any information about their past life circumstances.  We have all animals examined by a vet, brought up to date on shots, given their rabies vaccine, spayed/neutered (If old enough), wormed and checked for heartworms and if positive begin treatment.  We do our best to ensure that we are placing healthy pets but can make no guarantee to the health or temperament of this pet, and vet expenses are the responsibility of the adoptive family from the date of the adoption.  We require that you take the pet to a vet within one week of adoption for a check-up and to allow your vet to get a baseline for your new pet’s health.

animal.description: Approximate birthdate: 6/25/2020 approximate weight: 48lbs Howdy, I'm Allie and I already love you. I come from Texas, where there is no snow and I have to tell you that I was missing out! I can't get enough of it. It is so fun! I am potty trained and I sit patiently at the door when I need to go out. Have I told you yet that I love FOOD. It must be the puppy in my because sometimes I steal my foster siblings dog food. My foster mom says I am just a pup at around 7 months old and that I am all legs. She jokes that I might be part greyhound because I am so fast. I love everybody but do need slow introductions. Once I have met you, look out! I give endless hugs and kisses and I really want to sleep in bed with you. I believe the humans call it cuddling and I love it! I love my fur foster brothers but boy do I think the chickens are fun to chase, so I guess a home without them would be ideal. My adoption fee is $400.00 plus MN tax. This covers my spay and vaccinations up to the time of adoption. To apply please visit northernlakesrescue.org Breeds are best guess as we do not know who mom and dad are

animal.description: Approximate Birthdate: 1/15/2018 Approximate Weight: 11.8 lbs Hi, I'm Joey and I am 11 lbs of love and companionship! Even though I am just a little guy (with a big personality!), I get along great with my big dog friends. There's been a cat around too and I am not so sure about her. I feel like I should chase her, but I'm working on holding back. I came all the way from South of Houston, so I am not a big fan of the snow and the cold. I have a nice little coat that helps me stay warmer outside. Sometimes, I am nice and I pee outside, but this has been a work in progress. It's just so cold out there! I am motivated by treats (except anything with peanut butter), and learned SIT very quickly. We are working on more commands. I really like my kennel. It is my safe zone and I stay in there during the day while the humans are at work and at night, when we sleep. Some of my favorite things? Snuggling on the couch next to the humans! Be patient with me because I am afraid of shouts or raised voices. I am weary of males, but I just need a little bit of time to gain their trust. I can't wait to meet you! My adoption fee is $375.00 plus MN tax. This covers my neuter and vaccines up to the time of adoption. To apply please visit northernlakesrescue.org Breeds are best guess as we do not know who mom and dad are

animal.description: Welcome Leo to Lucky Dog Rescue. Leo a 1 year old white poodle miniature poodle weighing about 12lbs. Leo is part of the China Rescue Dogs mission to save 60 small breed dogs from the meat trade before the Chinese New Year celebrations. We know Leo was likely someone’s pet that was discarded in March or April after the start of COVID when it was wrongly believed that pets carried the virus. Not true! It was somewhere around this time he was rescued and placed in a foster home. For months Leo has been in a boarding facility getting up to date on his vaccinations, neuter ,quarantine, passport and then finally his flight to New York USA!! Leo arrived today  in Wisconsin and is the biggest love!! He is the happiest and sweetest boy! He loves everyone he meets. He does well with other dogs and surprisingly doesn’t have an resource guarding issues!! Leo is crate trained however he may not be receptive the crate after arrival. He will need help to reestablish housetraining after travel and being in a boarding facility. He does currently mark but with time may improve. He will come with belly bands that fit around his midsection and will help him with his marking issues. He is in perfect health and is fully up to date on all of his vaccinations, tests, and neuter. He will be microchipped and will be registered to Lucky Dog Rescue for the rest of his life. Leo’s adoption fee will not be inexpensive. Due to border closures and needing to fly cargo, his flight alone with all the fees without medical care was $500. We are asking $750 minimally but appreciate anything beyond that to help other China dogs. Leo’s entire fee will be going back to Chinarescuedogs.org to help get other dogs to freedom in the US. With all of our adoptions if at any point the adoption isn’t successful within the first two weeks the entire adoption fee is returned. After the two weeks of the dogs need to be rehomed for any reason the dogs must be returned to the rescue. Leo will be a great addition to any active household that can be patient with his re-housetraining.

animal.description:
COURTESY POST – LOLA IS NOT A SOHO DOG, AND IF YOU ARE INTERESTED IN ADOPTING HER YOU MUST CONTACT HER OWNER DIRECTLY AT beachmama1010@yahoo.com

Lola is a sweet, loving young Australian Shepherd who must find a new home.  Her owner rescued her from a difficult situation but is not allowed to permanently keep a dog in her current home.  Lola is just 20 months old, has a pretty blue merle coat, and she is a great weight at 40 pounds.  She is spayed, up to date on all of her vaccines and is on monthly preventatives.  Lola is housebroken, crate-trained and knows her basic obedience commands.  She walks nicely on leash and loves to ride in the car.
Lola loves people!  She is a high Velcro girl who loves to be wherever her people are.  Lola is also a medium to high energy dog who loves other dogs.  Lola enjoys so many different activities – fetching balls and toys, running and chase, tug of war, swimming, chasing birds, making noise with her squeaky toys – you name it!  And when all the fun is done Lola has a great “off switch”.  She loves belly rubs!  Lola has not been introduced to cats but given her prey drive her home should probably not include resident cats.
The ideal home for Lola is loving and active, shared with someone who is looking for a true best friend.  A fenced yard and another playful young dog would be ideal, and because children make her nervous her new home should include no children under the age of 12.  Lola deserves an amazing home, and if you are looking for an amazing Lola, please contact her owner directly at beachmama1010@yahoo.com.  Lola currently lives near Wilmington, NC.

animal.description:
Meet CHANCE! 

Chance is an approximately 7 year old male pittie or staffie mix.  He currently weighs around 60 lbs and is fully vetted. 

We believe that  he can be socialized with bigger dogs, not the tiny ones however.   Chance is very affectionate with people, especially someone he bonds with.  

Here is Chance's story prior to us saving him:  

Hello, my name is Chance, and I live all by myself in an empty house in Asheville, NC. It’s cold and lonely here, and I remember how much I have loved the companionship of human beings, cuddling on a coach to keep everyone warm. I lived for the last 7 years of my life with my Dad, who adopted me when I was a puppy. We were pals and lived a nice bachelor life, but a few months ago, my Dad moved me in with his girlfriend, who has a smaller dog. The smaller dog and I got into a scuffle and now I am never allowed to live with my Dad again. He comes to feed me once a day in this house I live in all alone and the nights are long and the days are cold. My Dad loves me as much as he knows how to, and does not want me to go to a shelter, where I’ll probably be forever lost. So, a nice lady stepped in who is trying to find me a home.  I can probably do okay with other dogs around my size, just not the little ones.  I do great with people, and I’d love a nice yard too.

Please help us give Chance the loving, forever home he deserves that won't abandon him again.   

If interested, please contact Christine at christinerescueexpress@gmail.com

animal.description:
Soul is an adorable tiny toy Chihuahua ready for his forever home. He is full of energy and very happy and playful. He is pure white and still under 3lbs at over 3 months of age so we anticipate he will stay very small. Soul has a "half" tail. It looks like it was docked but we are told he was born with it like that. He and his brother were surrendered by their owners so they could have their mother spayed. Soul will of course need training as he is just a young pup but he is cute and funny and will bring a family a lifetime of joy. 

Soul is a short coated breed so he will require regular nail trims but not necessarily professional grooming. 

Soul's adoption fee is $325

This fee includes at least one health exam at our veterinarian while in our care, altering, all vaccinations including rabies (as permitted by age), a pre-adoption professional grooming and a microchip with lifetime membership that never will cost you a fee. 
 All dogs also leave with a new collar and or harness and leash as well as a gift bag which includes among other things, a starter bag of the quality kibble that is being fed at the rescue.
Adoption fees also allow us the ability to put funds towards the next homeless or unwanted dog in need of rescue!

If you'd like to considered to for this adoption or any of our amazing rescues, please fill our the application with the help of this link. https://www.shelterluv.com/matchme/adopt/AZST/Dog.

We review each application carefully. Please understand that sometimes we get numerous applications for particular dogs and as a volunteer based rescue we do not always have the time to respond to each and every one. We do our best to choose the most suitable home for each dog based on their specific personality and needs. 

Due to Covid, we are very short handed and may not contact you for up to a week to set up a meet and greet if your application is chosen. We appreciate all applicants and do our best to pair ever dog and family for a successful and happy life.

animal.description:
Hi, my name is  Mindy Cali!

I am 10 weeks old and 16lbs (will be larger fully grown).  I am 1/4 English bulldog 1/4 Boston terrier and half super mutt mix. We think these pups will be medium to large 45-60#

These are very social and friendly puppies who love people and cats and kids.

Mindy Cali has your average puppy personality: silly, goofy, sweet, loving and AWESOME. 

Interested in becoming a forever home for Mindy Cali? Fill out our online adoption application: http://www.friendswithfourpaws.org/adoption-form.html This is the first step in our process, and we don't go any further without an application.

Find more adoptable pets, news and information on Instagram @friendswithfourpaws or our Facebook page Friends with Four Paws .

We put a lot of time and energy into processing our adoptions to find our babies the best fit home for them and you.  Please do not submit an application if you are not serious about adopting Mindy Cali.
We are so excited to work with you to find you a new forever friend, and Mindy Cali the perfect forever home, and appreciate you working with us.  

Our adoption fee is $525. This includes their spay/neuter surgery, full (age appropriate) vaccinations, microchip insertion and registration, deworming, heartworm testing and prevention, flea and tick prevention and travel expenses.

All of our dogs are rescued from local shelters and the general public. Each dog is then placed in a foster home where he/she is kept for quarantine, to ensure if the dog gets sick it can receive proper treatment. We have foster homes in the NJ/NY area waiting to receive their fosters. Once an animal has received an application or there's an adopter interested, we make arrangements for transport. If a dog is already in foster care in NYC/NJ, an adopter will be put in touch with the foster home AFTER an application is being processed.

Thank you in advance for your patience with our process and for making adoption YOUR option!
animal.name: Mindy Cali

animal.description:
Please contact JoEllen (sagdinfo@aol.com) for more information about this pet.Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

** This dog is in a foster home in San Antonio, TX. Prospective adopters must be able to travel to San Antonio to complete the adoption process. Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/ **
Jojo is a beautiful 3-month-old Blue Heeler blend who weighs approximately 3.6 pounds. Jojo is affectionate and has a playful nature. Her ideal owner should have experience with herding breeds as they often can require extra training and exercise than more sedentary breeds.
Please understand you are committing to providing a good home for her entire life (up to 15+ years or more.)
You must be committed to housebreaking, age-appropriate enrichment and exercise, leash training, grooming needs, and positive socialization.
Her adoption fee is $300. This includes her spay surgery, rabies vaccination, Nobivac Canine 1-DAPP vaccination, Nobivac Intra-Trac 3 vaccination, Drontal Plus, IDEXX SNAP 4Dx Plus Test, Tri-Heart Plus chewable tablet, 24PetWatch microchip, leash and collar, and a trial offer for 24PetWatch Pet Insurance.
Please be aware that puppies and small breed dogs do get adopted quickly so interested parties are encouraged to apply online at www.saspca.org.
Please ensure your application is complete before submitting. We do verify property ownership, landlord references, apartment/HOA restrictions, veterinary references, and criminal histories.
Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio TX 78232. Event hours are 11:00 a.m. to 3:00 p.m.
Additional questions may be directed to sagdinfo@gmail.com.
** This dog is in a foster home in San Antonio, TX. Prospective adopters must be able to travel to San Antonio to complete the adoption process. Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/ **

- IMPORTANT INFORMATION -

SASPCA Homeward Bound Dog Rescue and San Antonio Great Dane Rescue are 501(c)(3) foster-based rescue groups based in San Antonio, Texas.

Our group focuses on assisting open admission shelters in South Texas where over 32,000 dogs and cats are euthanized each year.

Our puppies and dogs are completely vetted and live in foster homes. They are spayed/neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, dewormed, and tested for heartworm disease.All adoptions include one month of flea and heartworm preventative, leash and collar, and opportunity to enroll in a 30-day trial of pet insurance.

Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio, TX 78232. Event hours are typically 11:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m.

We also host additional adoption events throughout the year. Please visit our Facebook pages for the most current event schedules.

https://m.facebook.com/HomewardBoundDogRescue/?tsid=0.11494693985281179&source=typeahead

https://m.facebook.com/profile.php?id=185497084826453&tsid=0.7626298417270982&source=typeahead

If your adoption application is approved and you are traveling from out-of-town, we hold your chosen pet for one hour past the event start time to allow for travel time.

We are an all-volunteer organization and do not currently have the resources to process out-of-state adoptions.

Our puppies, purebred dogs, and small breed dogs do get adopted quickly so we encourage interested parties to apply online.

Please apply here:

http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

animal.description:
McGee (CP)
**COURTESY POST - MCGEE IS WITH CURRENT OWNER UNTIL REHOMED

2/1/2021  Hi!  My name is McGee.  I am a two year old male Bull Terrier and Corgi mix with the prettiest blue eyes.  I am neutered, up to date on all of my vaccinations, and microchipped.  I know all of my basic commands and am a very fast learner.  My favorite past times are walks, hikes, and runs.  If you can't tell, I am a very active guy but love to snuggle any chance I get.  I like to be close to my person and will be right next to you whenever I can be.  Don't worry though!  I am crate trained and have no problem with alone time... just leave me some toys ;)  I LOVE treats and will go gaga for them.  However, I do not like to share.  I will do best in a home with no other dogs and no little kids.  I currently live with my human and a sister, Luna.  Unfortunately, Luna and I compete over food.  We are working very hard with a trainer but my human wants to keep her options open so I can have the best life possible.  I will only go to a new home if it is better than what my current human can offer.  If you are looking for an active cuddle bug, you might just be my perfect match! If interested in adopting McGee, please complete an application today at www.secondchanceforpets.com.

**NOT ALL PETS LISTED ON OUR WEBPAGE ARE IN OUR FOSTER HOMES. WE ALSO MAKE COURTESY POSTS (CP) FOR FAMILIES NEEDING TO PLACE THEIR PET. 
(SC) MEANS THEY ARE IN ONE OF OUR GROUPS FOSTER HOMES
(CP) MEANS THEY ARE STILL WITH THEIR CURRENT OWNER

animal.description:
Hi my name is Eclipse! I’m 3 years old and 30 lbs! 

I just arrived to ODHS but the humans promised to update my bio as they learn more about me! 

You can still come adopt me or even join our foster program to help the humans learn all the awesome things about new dogs like me! Learn more on our website! 

Hope to see you soon! 

What breed am I? Mixed mutt! ODHS does not breed label (unless there’s official paperwork), as studies show it is nearly impossible to tell the exact breed of each dog based off of their appearance.

Educational articles:
3/3/3 Rule;
https://www.rescuedogs101.com/bringing-new-dog-home-3-3-3-rule/?fbclid=IwAR2iv5m7fqk3FieO7LOsstGeGsYYV_F1rJOd1BPxaImofLpcinpYsUbFRWs

Adoption Donations are $250 for an adult, $350 for puppies (a dog under one year of age), and $125 for a senior dog (based on the age of the dog). Adoption donations are to be made via cash, and credit/debit card. There is a $5 fee to run cards.

Please remember to bring a collar and leash (non-retractable) with you the day of the adoption. Note: Martingale collars and slip leads are strongly recommended.

Due to COVID19, we aren't having as many open, public adoption events.  Current schedule is pre-determined meet and greet appointments are Wednesday evenings and on Saturdays. 
Our adoption center is located at 3602 Lafayette Blvd, Suite 102, Fredericksburg, VA 22408. It's important that you keep an eye on your emails for any changes or updates during the adoption process.

Visit our website for an application to adopt. 
https://www.olddominionhumanesociety.org/adoption-application

Old Dominion Humane Society is a volunteer based organization. We are run completely by volunteers, who also have full time jobs, so we appreciate your patience.  Currently, the average timeframe for a response to your application is 1 week.

Like us on Facebook "Old Dominion Humane Society"
and be a part of promoting forever homes for dogs in need.
#Adopt #Donate #Foster #Volunteer 

Note: ODHS only adopts to Virginia and surrounding states (including D.C.). A $50 out of state fee applies.

I do want to be an only child as I have been bullied by other dogs and they beat me up, but I have healed up really good, just a little nervous around other dogs...I just wanted to play! My foster brothers have been nice to me. Please share my picture because I know my forever mom and dad are looking for me. I sure wish they could find me. I am ready to be theirs forever. Thank you!

He's a little chihuahua. He was attacked by some dogs. His face has healed he has a little bit of a bum eye, but he is as sweet and as cute as can be and just needs a forever lap. He will expect lots of kisses and hugs and of course will return them as well. Let me know if you have a loving place in your heart and home for this sweet boy. He would do well in a home as the only dog as he now has trust issues with dogs. He gets along with small dogs with the correct introduction.

This boy has been let down too many times. He landed in a shelter and then was attacked by dogs there. He is so sweet but was so scared. 

All Dallas DogRRR adoptable pets are spayed or neutered, microchipped, and up to date on vaccines upon finalizing adoption. The standard minimum donation for puppies is $325 + 8.25% tax = $351.81, for dogs over 12 months the adoption fee is $225 + 8.25% tax = $243.66 and for our senior dogs 8 years and up is $100 + 8.25% tax = $108.25; this increase includes sales tax recently required by the State of Texas to collect. You can view all the adoptable pets and fill out an adoption application online on our website at http://dallasdogrrr.org. 

For more information, you can email adopt@dallasdogrrr.org. Upon receiving your application please allow us 2-3 business days to review and process.

animal.description: Since you're reading this, you're obviously looking for a new best friend-and, hey, so am I! I don't care how old you are or what you look like, but in case those things matter to you, I'm approximately a year old and that's me in the picture with the silky, soft fur and gorgeous eyes! My perfect match would be someone who loves spending time with their best friend, I'm down for anything, from movie dates on the couch to sky diving. I'm your ride or die. I don't mean to brag, but people tell me I'm a lot like LeonardoDiCaprio in The Titanic because I have stunning eyes and am completely devoted to those I love. When I'm not admiring your every move, I'd love to be playing with other dogs. So, what do you say? Wanna be besties? Do you want a dog who can live with kitties and not bother them? That's me! I don't bother kitties at all. Got kids? No problem, I love 'em! Sounds like I check all of your boxes, doesn't it!? If so, just fill out an application for me at www.pawsitivetailskc.org, and we can set up a time to meet! My adoption fee is $150 and I'm up to date on vaccines, dewormed, heartworm negative, current on flea and heartworm prevention, neutered and I'm even microchipped! Come meet me today, bestie!

animal.description:
Kavik boy is ready to steal someone's heart! <3

"Kavik is a handsome little guy. He has the cutest little dot on the middle of his head. Kavik is a mix of playful and calm. He is a bit more independent than his siblings, but still enjoys cuddles. He is outgoing and typically one of the first ones out of the kennel. Kavik has the kind of personality that would fit into pretty much any household! <3" 

Kavik is a 6 week old male Great Pyrenees mix. He currently weighs about 10lbs. Our best guess is he will top out somewhere in the 80-90lb range. 

-Kavik has been with us since birth. His mom Varity came to us heavily pregnant. We are unsure of who his dad was. Varity's former owner believes it was a male Pyr mix who visits sometimes but doesn't know for sure. 

-Kavik is still a baby. This means his new family needs to be ready to potty train him, work with him on basic manners, and have a lot of time on their hands to help raise him. 

-Kavik will need proper socialization. His new family will need to expose him to a little bit of everything. Such as walks, car rides, public outings, visitors, other dogs, etc. 

-Kavik will not be ready to go home until February 22, give or take a couple of days. Anyone applying to adopt him needs to be able to bring him home close to that date. 

-Kavik is being fostered in Kiowa, OK. We do not send our dogs on transports or ship them. This means his new family needs to pick him up, even if they are out of state. 

Want to make this cutie pie yours? Apply to adopt him at https://www.pyrpawsandfluffytailsrescue.com/adoption-app

His adoption fee is $275. That includes two sets of puppy shots, bordetella, and rabies. He will be micro-chipped, have a fecal done, be de-wormed, be spayed/neutered, and will be current on my heart-worm and flea/tick prevention.

animal.description:
Please contact Pet (information@pethelpersinc.org) for more information about this pet.

Hi my name is Zoey and I'm a 6 years old corgie mix. I'm a very sweet girl. I get along with all the dogs and cats in my foster home. I'm not fond of little children but teenagers can be ok. I'm very shy and it takes a bit for me to trust you. But once you show me you love me and feed me treats I do come around and follow you everywhere. I am house and crate trained. I'm not a fan of a crate but I do get used to it. I can do a few tricks. I sit and beg(mom says sit up). I could learn more with work. I can be very nervous at going outside at first so a good fenced yard is important. I've been vetted, spayed, microchipped and flea treated. If you would like a girl like me then complete an application here
https://www.pethelpersinc.org/adoption-application/
. And the adoption fee is $150.

For more information on this animal email adoptionisforever@pethelpersinc.org.

Pet Helpers is a 501(c)(3) nonprofit foster based volunteer rescue located in Fairmont, WV. We do adopt out of state to approved applicants, if you are willing to drive to WV to pick up your pet. We do not fly or use transport companies. Our adoption fee is $150.00 for mixed breed puppies and adult dogs, $225.00 for full blooded puppies and adult dogs and $50.00 for cats and kittens. Regardless if the animal is a mixed breed or full blooded they are spayed/neutered prior to adoption IF they are old enough. If they are too young at the time of adoption, then it is your financial responsibility to spay/neuter the pet by the age of 6 months and you must provide proof for our files that it has been done. All of our pets are checked by a vet, given the shots appropriate for their age and any other treatment deemed necessary by the vet. All of our pets are adopted as indoor pets and are not be outdoors tied to a box 24/7. The pet you are adopting has been living in a home with a foster family. You are expected to take possession of the pet you are applying for within a few days of application approval. This will enable us to accept another pet into that home. Because we are a rescue, and believe that spaying and neutering is crucial in stopping the reproduction of unwanted puppies/kittens and massive amounts of animals dying daily in shelters across the country, we expect any animal already in your home to be spayed/neutered. If for any reason you are unable to keep the pet you have adopted you are required to return them to Pet Helpers, Inc. They are not to be sold or given away.

Check us out on Facebook!!!!!! We hope you will give us two paws up, like our page and share with your friends. Pet Helpers, Inc.

animal.description:
Isn’t two always better than one? When it comes to cuteness in smaller packages, we’ve got that covered. We are dynamic duo Henry and Millie - a bonded pair of miniature Australian Shepherds. We were found running down a street. No one claimed us so we are now looking for our forever home! If you are looking for cuddles, tons of moments of cuteness, softness and more cuddles, we are the puppies you have been looking for.
Henry is approximately 8 years old and 25 lbs. Millie is 6 years old and 18 lbs. It’s clear someone took care of us and did some training. We are typical herding dogs, and need to make sure we are in charge of what’s happening. 
We love having a crate to den in and puppy beds. Millie loves her toys. She will flip them in the air and retrieve like a labrador! She also loves to guard her toys and makes lots of noise if other puppies come by them. It’s all noise. She also LOVES to cuddle on your lap belly up in the air for rubs. Henry is also a lab buddy. He can jump very high and may land in your lap at any time so be ready! Henry is a couch potato. A flat pillow on the couch is the perfect perch for him. 
We are quite smart and understand several commands. We are very treat motivated. We are fully potty trained – you can say go potty and we will run outside and potty immediately. We come when called. Millie is quite the character, she loves to pull toys under the table when she thinks no one is looking. And if you say Millie Bell in a high pitched voice, she will wiggle her whole butt and look at you like you are the most loved human in the world. We both really enjoy when you sit on the floor with us.
We are pretty perfect, but we do have a couple things that need work. We bark if we hear a lot of activity happening in the yard but interestingly don’t bark at the doorbell and don’t bark if we go by houses with barking dogs. We walk well on a leash, but we are reactive barkers when we see people or dogs. If you turn us in the other direction and redirect our attention, we calm down quickly. It will take some consistent training to get us past this. Apartment living or tight living quarters with a lot of activity will not be a good fit for us. Henry can be a little fussy with some men. He does best if you let him come to you first as he is getting to know you. He has done very well with his foster dad and foster grandpa. It just takes him a little while to settle in and then he will begin to come by with finger licks. Small children are likely not a good fit due to the tendency for quick movements that could cause anxiety.  
If you are looking for lots of cuddles and can provide a loving environment, we can complete your family and bring you so much joy.   Adoption fee:  $400 for both.  For more information, please email:  Avrisundell@gmail.com

Available for adoption Wednesday February 3rd at 7:00pm on our website under the Adoptions Uncrated program, followyourheartanimalrescue.org/shop

I've been calling her Elby as in ""LB"" AKA little babe AKA la beb. 

She's roughly 2 years old, great with dogs and cats and people. She's almost house trained, she wasn't sure how to ask to go out at first but with consistency she should be trained pretty easily. She settles quickly in her kennel now that she has settled into my routine. She walks great on a leash, has been my shadow the last few days and loves demanding pets by pushing her cold nose under your hand.

She does have a habit of jumping up for attention, petting, and during any excitement. She corrects easily and with consistency you could break this habit, I would be mindful of young kids due to it. She will also jump up to check out what's on the counter or table. - foster mom Mackenzie

animal.description:
Meet Aurora! This little low rider is the sweetest, maybe some bassett or corgi in her because her little legs bring her so close to the ground. In Roman mythology, Aurora is the goddess of sunrise, which makes sense because this girl will bring nothing but sunshine to your life! Aurora is one of the shelters newest residents, but trust us when we say she won’t be with us for long! It doesn’t take any time at all to realize that Aurora is a perfect companion for any family. She’s sweet, smart, and so loving. She’ll crawl right up into your lap and give a kiss, but when you’re ready to play, she’ll be right by your side for any adventure you have in mind. We can tell she’s a young girl, but she is wise beyond her years. She has a beautiful brindle coat with the perfect white accents on all four of her feet, her belly, and the tips of her nose and tail. Ask us how to meet this goddess today!
Please stop by the City of Jackson Animal Shelter at 140 Outer Circle, Jackson, MS during their adoption hr (10 - 4 M - F and 8:30-10:30 Sat) to meet Aurora and take a leash with you so that you can take her outside for a walk and get to know her a little better.  For more information, please contact Kristianna (a volunteer with Jxn Friends of the Animal Shelter) via phone (410-924-1053) or email (ksaelensybk2@yahoo.com). Aurora is eligible for a free spay thru Jackson Friends of the Animal Shelter.  For more pictures and information, please take a look at our Jackson Friends of the Animal Shelter page on Facebook.

Agima is 40 lbs, is 2 years old..was found when 6 weeks old, loves to instigate play & she runs like the wind!  She is the imp. (I found Agima early one morning when I arrived at school. She was maybe 6 weeks old. She went to the front door of the school and just sat there, wouldn’t leave.  I begged others to please take her as I already had a handful.  But if i didn’t take her, the school guards would remove her and put her somewhere. So I took her home and she joined Mika. In June we take our students camping. I had no one to look after Mika and Agima, so they came camping.  They were so well behaved and the kids loved having them)

 We do not know breed mix of these 3 dogs. The arrival is planned for Feb. 27th into JFK, then transported to Raleigh. We are looking for fosters or 'foster to adopt' w/ the knowledge that the meet on Sunday may be late at night & we will have vet apts for them to keep that week! They are fully vetted.
***
Thank you for your interest in our rescues ! Events most every weekend, Saturdays, to meet some. All may be met by appointment w/ approved application. Facebook posts who will attend (current week).  Available dogs, donation button(we are non-profit) & links to adopt/volunteer www.lovemuttsrescue.org . We will email you our process & fees. When one is in "foster to adopt", they are taken off our website, but may be relisted w/in 2 weeks, if not a final adoption. Blessings, The Love Mutts Rescue Team

animal.description: # 705770 Age: 5 years Weight: 14.9 lbs How this pet arrived:This pet was brought in by a Good Samaritan on January 21, 2020.Why this pet is the one for you: Meet Sleepy everyone! He has come along away and our trainers are excited by the progress he has made while being in our care. He was very afraid when he arrived and it took a while for him to gain the trust of his caregivers. He is slowly getting his confidence back and he is ready for his new best friend! Once given the chance to warm up, you will see what a bouncy, silly and loving little companion he can be! Sleepy is looking forward to continuing his positive reinforcement and positive association training with his new family. Sleepy would do best in an small, adult home with a family that can listen to direction. Older teenagers might be okay if they know how to read dog body language! Sleepy came in with his siblings but his confidence only improved once he was separated from them. He would be happiest as the only dog in the home. We think he wants all the love and attention for himself! Sleepy can't wait to find his new best friend. Could it be you he has been waiting for? PLEASE COMPLETE OUR ADOPTION APPLICATION AT WWW.LOVEBUGSRESCUE.ORG IF YOU’D LIKE TO BE CONSIDERED FOR ADOPTION:

We found Tumbleweed at the Moreno Valley shelter, and when we laid eyes on her there was no turning back. Tumbleweed is a 13 year young 12 lb soft coat terrier that immediately caught the eye of one of our fosters who has a soft spot for the oldies but goodies. Tumbleweed is such a gentle and sweet gal. Not to mention she's pretty darn cute with her tussle of silver hair. 

Tumbleweed makes a great co-pilot and enjoys going for car rides and running errands with her foster mommy. She is an easy going gal and is well mannered in the home. She is doing great with her potty routine, but we expect a few accidents when transitioning to a new home. Tumbleweed gets along well with other dogs, cats and new people she meets. She walks well on leash, and would love to continue those with her new family. 

Tumbleweed can only hear loud noises, but her heart is in great shape, her eyesight is good and she got an A+ on her bloodwork. Her vetting is complete which includes a dental, so her mouth is in kissable shape when she meets you. The ideal home for Tumbleweed would be a home on the quiet side with someone who enjoys going for walks and cuddle time on the couch. An owner who is looking for a sweet senior to spend their golden years with. Could that be you?

Tumbleweed’s adoption fee is $150 and that includes her spay, registered microchip, vaccines current, deworming, flea treatment and her dental. Apply to meet her at www.lovebugsrescue.org

animal.description:
Roxy has the heart of an emotional support dog. If you are looking for an animal to strongly bond with and wants to cuddle all the time then look no further! Roxy is a 50lb lap dog who loves to play and be a couch potato with you. Everyone who meets her falls in love and so will you. Roxy has had a rough couple years, she was surrendered by her first owner because the other dogs she lived with started bullying her and Roxy wouldn’t defend herself thus leading to injuries (successfully treated by her veterinarian). Roxy’s new owner then had her world change when they moved back with family while their home was being built. The chaos was too much for all the dogs and Roxy ended up surrendered again. Roxy is perfect and her perfect home is quiet, only dog or small dogs, she loves kids and is great with cats too! Please consider giving Roxy her forever home! She was born in 2016 and is located in a foster home. 

Included with adoption: Age-appropriate vaccinations, up to date heart-worm preventative, heart-worm test if over 6 months, insurance for 30 days, microchip with registration, and spayed or neutered- if not already, a voucher is provided.

animal.description:
{s3829code380/}
If you would like to provide this dog a loving home, please fill out a pre-adoption application.

Have a question? Please read our Frequently Asked Questions and Adoption Processed Explained documentation.
_________ B I O ______________

Name:Jonesy
Size: (Once fully grown) ~Large range: 61-100 lbs
Adoption Donation:$250 (applicable sales tax included) PLUS a $100 deposit is required and is to be refunded once proof of spay/neuter is provided to this rescue. Our adoption contract requires all dogs to be spayed/neutered within ONE Month of adoption or when age-appropriate.Adoption fees may be paid by cash or check.
Other:Intact Male, Vaccinations current, Microchip, Not apartment-friendly

Puppies generally need the following veterinary care after their adoption:

8 Weeks:Distemper/Parvo & Bordetella Vaccinations. Luv of Dog Rescue completes these vaccinations before adoption.
12 Weeks:Distemper/Parvo Vaccination, completed at the veterinarian of adopter's choice.
16 Weeks:Distemper/Parvo Vaccination, Rabies Vaccination, completed at the veterinarian of adopter's choice.
6 Months:Spay/Neuter surgery. 
Yearly thereafter:All dogs need yearly wellness exams performed by a veterinarian as well as booster vaccinations.

~Spay/Neuter surgeries cost between $150-$250 for a neuter and $300-$400 for a spay surgery in the FM Area.Wellness visits can run from $50 to $100 for each visit. If you are thinking of adopting a puppy, it's a good idea to research these costs before adopting by calling the veterinarian of your choice.

Jonesy would love to grow up to be a well-trained and loved boy!

Foster Home Feedback

1/31/21: Jonesy has been a pleasure to have in our home for the past couple of weeks. He has lots of puppy energy so a playmate to help him burn off the energy would be best. He is a loud barker and barks a lot while playing so an apartment would probably not be the best place for him. Jonesy also knows how to just relax and hang out as well, which is nice.

Jonesy is working on potty training and has gone a couple of weeks without pooping in the house! He does still struggle with peeing outside but if you watch him and he looks like he is going to pee, we ask if he needs to go potty and he will wait to go until he is outside.

Jonesy loves to chew and sometimes needs reminders to only chew on toys and bones. He doesn't typically nap much in the morning but will nap quite a bit in the afternoon. Jonesy likes to fight sleep and will get kind of naughty if he is too tired. He does best if someone sits with him and helps him settle down so he can sleep.

Jonesy prefers to be close to his people so he sleeps in his kennel right by the bed. He sleeps mostly through the night but sometimes wakes up but he will go back to sleep after a few minutes.To view additional dogs available for adoption, please see our website: www.4luvofdog.org

animal.description:
ADOPT ME ONLINE: https://ophrescue.org/dogs/10393

Well hello there!

I'm Kuaka Bay from the National Parks Litter. I came to OPH and my foster home after a REALLY long ride and I am ready to find my best forever home!

I am currently living with my foster family, learning all kinds of fun things but it's time. Time for me to find my forever family. 
My foster mom says I am the largest of the boys at 6.4 pounds, and also the leader of the pack. I like to play with sticks and chew toys but don't worry, I love to be held and loved on too. I am just a baby at 9 weeks old so I am going to need your help to learn all those good doggie things like going potty outside, walking on a leash, not chewing things that are not mine and lots more. Are you up for the challenge to teach me? I promise, I'll be your best friend forever. Don't wait too long, I'll be here will you fill out the adoption application.

I am just a baby and my adopters should be respectful of my small size and puppy needs, such as not being left alone for more than 4 hours at a time, and to teach me proper manners with play, potty, leash walking and crating. In return, I promise to try really hard to make you proud and to give lots of puppy kisses!

Please note that because this puppy is so young, it has only received 2 of the required 3 puppy distemper vaccinations. This is very IMPORTANT because it means that the immune system will not be fully functioning until about 16 weeks of age. Until then, the puppy MUST stay out of public places where it could be exposed to the germs of other dogs. These no puppy zones include all pet stores, dog parks, and for apartment dwellers, areas used by other dogs. These requirements are strictly for the puppys medical safety and longevity.

This puppy is microchipped and up to date on age appropriate vaccines and monthly preventatives.
To adopt this dog, or any OPH dog, fill out the simple online application at https://ophrescue.org 
Operation Paws for Homes, Inc. (OPH) rescues dogs of all breeds and ages from high-kill shelters in NC, VA, MD, and SC, reducing the numbers being euthanized. With limited resources, the shelters are forced to put down 50-90% of the animals that come in the front door. OPH provides pet adoption services to families located in VA, DC, MD, PA and neighboring states. OPH is a 501(c)(3) organization and is 100% donor funded. OPH does not operate a shelter or have a physical location. We rely on foster families who open their homes to give love and attention to each dog before finding a forever home.

animal.description:
Meet Gabbi - 
3 years old, Fun, loving and affectionate girl - gabbi enjoys snuggles in all forms.  
Gabbi is very easy to care for.  She has great leash walking skills, is kennel trained, and muzzle trained.  Gabbi is tolerant of other dogs out side of the home but due to her possible past traumas we feel she would do best being the only dog in the home.  

When Gabbi came into our care she was suffering from allergies, since switching to a fish based diet her skin has improved tremendously.  Ideally , raw may be a good option for Gabbi in the future.  

Gabbi is best suited from a home that has no cats.  She has not been tested with small children but due to her playful energy and lack of personal space, Gabbi would be best suited for a home with kids 10 and up.  Gabbi loves the great outdoors so a home with a wood fenced yard is best suited for her. Breed experience is preferred.

If you are interested in Gabbi and feel she would be the perfect addition to your home please apply at; 
https://icefoundationk9rescue.ca/how-to-help/adopt/

At this time no all applications can be answered. If you no meet the criteria then please do not apply

Only dog
10+yrs kids
House 
Not cats
Previous experience with tough breed or mill dog experience.

--ABOUT KOPI--
Kopi is a happy-go-lucky big girl looking for a family who will take her on plenty of adventures followed by crashing on the couch together! She has many loves; car rides, swimming, and fetch to name a few. Her previous family helped her learn how to be a properly loved companion; she's housebroken, happy to greet everyone, and learned a lot of tricks! When the stress and chaos of moving out of state caused her to begin acting up with the child in the home the hard decision was made to have Kopi find a new home. While it was devastating, Kopi has stayed optimistic! Her days are full of running with the other pups, going on walks with the humans, and snuggling into her bed with plenty of toys. She's eager to find her new adult-only family to spoil her with even more play and cuddles. She would make an amazing hiking partner and thrive in more advanced training like agility!

Key Notes:
-2-year old spayed female.
-Labrador retriever mix.
-Around 70 pounds and a healthy weight.
-Brought to Buddy Dog when the stress of moving caused her to start pushing around the child in her home.
-No apartment style homes or small homes. A fenced-in yard is ideal.
-Needs and adult only (18+) home. Visiting children okay with supervision.
-Plays great with other dogs closer to her size!
-No more than 6 hours alone a day; will need a potty and play break for longer.
-Medium energy; loves playtime followed by relaxing by the TV with her family.
-Housebroken and crate trained.
-Learning proper leash walking but still pulls a bit.
-Food motivated; knows many tricks!
-Loves car rides, walks, swimming, and fetch.
-Would thrive in advanced training for fun!

animal.description: Hi there! My names Hoku. I'm a sweet energetic puppy looking for a home who will dedicate their time to training and exercise. Because of my excitement, some people might not like me jumping on them!! Which I get, but I do need help with training on that since I am so used to doing it. I love meeting new people; I will just soak in all the attention you give me. So, I LOVE toys!! So much. Squeaky toys, tennis balls, ropes... strings!! You name it. I love to share too because it means you'll play with me. Although, I do play tug and my handler says that's a no-no! Can you teach me why? Speaking of things I love... I love food and rawhide. I don't mind sharing those either. I'm a smart girl too, I know sit! I would love to learn more things since I am highly treat and toy motivated. Although, no tiny fingers because I take them a little roughly. When I meet another dog, I get so excited!! I run and pull and jump towards the other dogs! Some of them may not like it, which I understand but cannot comprehend! I think I just need further socialization with other dogs. Overall, I think I would do best in a home with no small children, probably no one under the age of 13 due to my jumpiness and high arousal levels. I also need a home dedicated to training and exercise. I hope to meet you soon!!

**Courtesy Listing-please contact them directly**

Meet Franklin! Franklin (also responds to Frankie and Frank) is a 65lb, Australian Shepherd/ Chocolate Labrador mix. He is 4 years old, neutered, and in good health with all vaccines up to date. We are looking for a forever home for Frank that can give him the love, attention, and action he needs and deserves. Frank is an extremely smart, loyal, and loving boy who loves nothing more than a game of fetch. Ok, maybe he loves getting a treat as much as a game of fetch. Frank has passed basic obedience training with flying colors since he was a pup. He is great off-leash and will 'sit', 'stay', 'down', 'leave it', and 'come' with near-perfection, and has the capability to learn far more skills if put in the time and effort. Frank loves being outside and loves any activity, including hiking, swimming, playing in the snow, fetch, 'search & rescue' with his ball, etc. Frank is quite independent and prefers the company of humans over other dogs. He has also shown fear towards children. Frank would do best in a home with acreage, without small children (ages 12 and under) and where he was the only dog, however if there was another adult dog with similar independent demeanor it may still be a good fit. Frank doesn't have much experience with cats or livestock but could be open to a meeting. Please, no condo or apartment living. Frank currently lives in Bend, Oregon.
Please contact via email with any questions or interest at alexjanadoza@gmail.com

THIS IS A COURTESY LISTING. HUNAH IS NOT PLACING THIS DOG. PLEASE CONTACT THE OWNER DIRECTLY.

animal.description:
If you're looking for a playful, affectionate, silly, happy, big kid of a dog - O'Henry could be the right match for you. He's a handsome guy with a lot of envious skills, he is house trained, crate trained, doesn't pull on the leash, he's treat motivated and comes when called. He's a really good boy with overall good manners.

O'Henry has a lot of energy, and would be best suited to an owner who would enjoy having an active dog around to take on big walks and hikes. He walks nicely on the leash, but he does have a strong prey drive...so stay alert to make sure you see those squirrels before he does!

O'Henry is at his absolute happiest when he is playing with his toys, or running around being goofy with other doggy pals.

There's a few puppy-like habits that he still needs to be trained out of...let's just say there has been the odd thing in his foster home that has a few O'Henry teeth marks on it, and he needs to learn that they're not his chew toys! He's an intelligent boy, and he loves to please his humans, so we think with training this will improve.

O'Henry is 2 years old, 58 lbs, and ready for his forever home! Please visit www.liveloveanimalrescue.org to fill out an adoption application.

animal.description:
Hello,

My name is Ranger. I am a 75 lb adult (4-7 yr old) German Shepard mix. I think I am closer to the younger side in that age range.

When I first came to K9, I was extremely underweight and heartworm positive. For me, it would best if any children in the home were over 13 years of age. I have been treated for heartworm and am feeling much better now. Slowly but surely I am getting closer to the weight I should be. I will sit patiently and wait for my food and accept treats gently when offered. I will also take my pills easily with a hotdog or peanut butter. I will eat all my dry dog food whenever my bowl is filled. If my foster family gives me any table food like scrambled eggs or meat scraps, I like to carry my bowl into the area they are eating to eat my special food with them. They think it’s the funniest thing in the world.

I am a big teddy bear and crave closeness from my family. I like to do what they are doing. Sitting on the couch and getting booty and belly rubs is amazing.

In my foster home, there is only a bird. I leave the bird alone. I seem to be interested in other dogs. Another dog in the home could be great for me. If you have another dog in your home let’s do a meet and greet and see how we do together.

I like all toys but I am especially fond of rope toys. I will spend a lot of time taking apart the rope. Tennis balls are another good toy for me. I’m getting pretty good at dropping them when you ask me to.

I have done well with potty training overall. A few accidents in the beginning til I learned where I was suppose to go potty. Be patient and diligent with me up front and I’ll pick up on potty training in your home in no time.

I have only gone on a few car rides so far but they were fun for me. I just sat in the back seat and looked out the window. Occasionally, I also would lay down too.

I really enjoy meeting new people and getting extra attention. I mean who doesn’t? I’m an attention-hog so I have discovered if I greet everyone with a smile on my face I get more pets.

I come pretty well when my foster family calls my name. It doesn’t take much for me come back by their side. Even when I am outside exploring the fenced yard, they call and I come running to see them.

I have free range of the house for bed time but I seem to like to sleep on the floor behind the couch. I am not that interested in sleeping on my doggie bed or in my foster families’ bedrooms. I may start in there but I tend to leave after a little while.

Leash walking is going great! I just love walks! I get pretty excited when I realize I'm going on a walk but I sit patiently while my foster family puts my harness on me. Now that I'm feeling better, I am pulling on the leash a little bit at first but I settle down pretty quickly.  I also like to bark a little bit at first to see if any of my neighbor dog friends are around to talk to.

I am having the best time eating the snow. I also like jumping and playing with the snow. I’m well-mannered and respectful of the boundaries I have been taught. I have not jumped on the counter or chewed on things that were not my dog toys. I think that is pretty good if you ask me. I love to be near my foster family, while they work at home or when we go play in yard. It’s all great! I would enjoy a fenced yard if you have one. Now I just need to find the forever home of my dreams.
 
If you think we could be a good match and you are over 21 years old, send in an application for me at k9stray.com. My friends at K9 will be in touch.

I can’t wait to meet you!

~Ranger
