animal.description:
NOTE:  The mailbox petfinder sends the "Ask About" email inquiries to is not as closely monitored as the email address applications go to.   That feature is a default with petfinder, and is not a part of our adoption process.

The first step in our adoption process is the application.  Completed applications take priority over inquiries.  To apply to adopt, please copy and paste the following url:

https://fs30.formsite.com/legacygsd/form4/index.html

Introducing Jack!  Jack is a (purebred) Anatolian Shepherd. His birthday is 8/15/19. He is 98lbs.

Jack was an owner surrender. His family lived out in the country. They didn't have a fence and Jack was left to roam. The neighbor did not appreciate Jack wandering onto his property and threatened to shoot him. The family tried Jack on a chain but a hearding breed does not do well with that type of setup.  Jack became depressed.  They decided that it was in Jack's best interest to surrender him to rescue to find a more suitable home with a fenced yard where Jack can enjoy the outdoors safely. 

Jack is a gentle giant. He is such a sweet boy!  He is well mannered.  He loves the outdoors but is also learning that being inside a home is also pretty awesome!  Jack is very laid back but also likes to get out there and romp and play when appropriate. He's BFF is Copper and the love playing and being goofy together. Jack has been around dogs 60lbs and up.  We can cat test him upon request. Jack has been around children 12 and up.

Jack is up to date on vaccines, has been tested for heartworms and 5 diseases spread by ticks, was tested/treated for ehrlichia, had entropian in both eyes but he's had the surgery to repair them, is neutered and microchipped. Jack is on monthly heartworm and flea/tick prevention.

As with all of our dogs, we recommend a basic obedience class to help him understand what is expected of him, and this also helps with the bonding process. 

Jack’s adoption fee is $475, which covers all his vetting, preventatives, fostering costs and other associated expenses.  We do not adopt to anyone under the age of 21.

animal.description:
Single Blue Female ISO of that special somebody or bodies with a cozy home so we can build our perfect, forever life together. I prefer gentle people with patience that won't give up on me if I make a mistake. I will try my hardest to do my best and make you happy. You see, I used to live out in the woods, alone for years. Around 3 lonely years if I had to guess. People tried to get me but at that time I did not know I wanted to be gotten. I have spent some time learning all things dog, but I can be a touch shy and new things can make me nervous at first. I love cuddles, food, stuffy toys with a squeaker and naps in any order or combination. I do the 'kangaroo Dance' when it's time to eat and make a noise like a hungry alien when I know someone else is eating and leaving me out of the equation. I DON'T like being out in the rain, vacuum cleaners and brooms. Cars are ok, they still freak me out a little. Walks were tough to learn, you know that whole leash thing felt weird and then we go places that are new and you know what I said about that new stuff. I am doing really well with it though. I like walking with other dogs, but I can do it by myself now too. I don't pull or act all crazy when I see another dog like some of my weird foster siblings. I keep asking them what all the fuss is about? I can walk with tons of dogs but prefer my home crew to be smaller and quieter. I can be friends with boy dogs or girl dogs as long as they're not too silly, bouncy and loud. I am quiet in my crate, well usually quiet in general but will give a good bark if I feel like something fishy is going on outside or in another room. I'm a pretty cool girl that needs someone who will understand that moving may be hard on me at first, that I need a little structure and that I am continuing to learn what it means to be comfortable with all the things the world has to offer. I am about 6 years old but really I am not sure because I didn't get a birthday party until I was rescued. Are you the special somebody I have been searching for? We can celebrate our birthdays together if you like? Please let the humans know if you have any other questions. ---Love Matilda

If you are interested in adopting Matilda, please fill out an application today!

animal.description:
NOTE:  The mailbox petfinder sends the "Ask About" email inquiries to is not as closely monitored as the email address applications go to.   That feature is a default with petfinder, and is not a part of our adoption process.

The first step in our adoption process is the application.  Completed applications take priority over inquiries.  To apply to adopt, please copy and paste the following url:

https://fs30.formsite.com/legacygsd/form4/index.html

Introducing Tally!  Tally is a 15 week old Plott Hound/Mix.  She is currently 14lbs and will be a medium size dog full grown.

Tally came to rescue from a shelter in rural MS.  She was originally picked up as a stray and no one claimed her.  After a 72 hr "stray hold" the shelter can and will euthanize dogs and puppies. We couldn't let that be this cutie patootie's fate so we sent a volunteer to scoop her up on her "due out" day.

Tally is a sweet girl. She is a little shy when meeting new people but warms quickly. She is doing great in her foster home.  Tally has become a snuggle bug and loves getting TLC from her foster mom.  She has learned that beds and blankets are fantastic!  She is learning her house manners and doing well with her house training.  She is good with other dogs and get along with all the other canines in her foster home.  She is curious about cats but she got popped on the nose by the cat at the vet clinic we use she decided that maybe cats aren't that friendly.  She has been around children school age and up.  

Tally is up to date on age appropriate vaccines, tested for intestinal parasites and treated accordingly, is on monthly heartworm and flea/tick prevention, is spayed and microchipped.

As with all of our dogs, we recommend a basic obedience class to help her understand what is expected of her, and this also helps with the bonding process. 

Tally's adoption fee is $475, which covers all her vetting, preventatives, fostering costs and other associated expenses.  We do not adopt to anyone under the age of 21.

Brooks is a chihuahua mix around a year and a half old. He is a very sweet boy who has spent the majority of his life not being socialized or had much training so we are working on those things with him before he is able to be adopted. What we do know is although he is shy, he LOVES his people including kids! He would do best in a calmer household, with a family that has plenty of time for him. We are working very hard on both house and crate training, but we aren't fully there yet. He does okay with other dogs his size, but doesn't like bigger dogs or high energy dogs in his face.

If interested please visit our website to view the process and fill out an application. W2rescueflorida.org

animal.description:
Sweet Wilma is being fostered in PA.
 
This is what Wilma's foster mom has to say about Wilma:
Wilma is a super sweet 14 week old Black Lab/Boxer mix. She has average energy, so not hyper, but does love to play. Then she cuddles next to you or on you for a nap. Wilma loves to cuddle! She is almost completely house broken. She goes in her crate and is given a small bully stick and she will chew that till she falls asleep, and sleeps through the night.
Wilma is very smart and already knows SIT, and automatically sits for her food. She is learning OFF and LEAVE IT. Wilma just wants to please. Wilma will make a great, loving and loyal companion for someone.
BDRA has voted against the use of electrical fencing effective immediately
